\n138: \n139: **Description:** Rotates the refresh token and issues a new access token. Old refresh token is revoked.\n140: \n141: **Request Body:** none (reads `refresh_token` from httpOnly cookie)\n142: \n143: **Success Response** `200 OK`:\n144: ```json\n145: {\n146:   \"success\": true,\n147:   \"statusCode\": 200,\n148:   \"message\": \"Token refreshed successfully\",\n149:   \"data\": {\n150:     \"user\": {\n151:       \"id\": \"uuid\",\n152:       \"name\": \"string\",\n153:       \"email\": \"string\",\n154:       \"role\": \"renter | admin\"\n155:     }\n156:   },\n157:   \"timestamp\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\",\n158:   \"path\": \"/api/auth/refresh\"\n159: }\n160: ```\n161: \n162: **Error Responses:**\n163: - `401` — Missing, expired, or revoked refresh token\n164: \n165: ---\n166: \n167: #### Forgot Password\n168: \n169: | Method | Path | Auth |\n170: |--------|------|------|\n171: | `POST` | `/auth/forgot-password` | Public |\n172: \n173: **Description:** Sends a password reset email with a secure reset token. Always returns 200 regardless of whether the email exists (prevents enumeration).\n174: \n175: **Request Body:**\n176: ```json\n177: {\n178:   \"email\": \"string (required)\"\n179: }\n180: ```\n181: \n182: **Success Response** `200 OK`:\n183: ```json\n184: {\n185:   \"success\": true,\n186:   \"statusCode\": 200,\n187:   \"message\": \"If an account with that email exists, a password reset link has been sent\",\n188:   \"data\": null,\n189:   \"timestamp\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\",\n190:   \"path\": \"/api/auth/forgot-password\"\n191: }\n192: ```\n193: \n194: **Error Responses:**\n195: - `400` — Invalid email format\n196: \n197: ---\n198: \n199: #### Reset Password\n200: \n201: | Method | Path | Auth |\n202: |--------|------|------|\n203: | `POST` | `/auth/reset-password` | Public |\n204: \n205: **Description:** Resets the user's password using a valid reset token.\n206: \n207: **Request Body:**\n208: ```json\n209: {\n210:   \"token\": \"string (required)\",\n211:   \"password\": \"string (min 8 chars, required)\"\n212: }\n213: ```\n214: \n215: **Success Response** `200 OK`:\n216: ```json\n217: {\n218:   \"success\": true,\n219:   \"statusCode\": 200,\n220:   \"message\": \"Password reset successfully\",\n221:   \"data\": null,\n222:   \"timestamp\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\",\n223:   \"path\": \"/api/auth/reset-password\"\n224: }\n225: ```\n226: \n227: **Error Responses:**\n228: - `400` — Validation failed or expired token\n229: - `404` — Invalid token\n230: \n231: ---\n232: \n233: #### Get Current User\n234: \n235: | Method | Path | Auth |\n236: |--------|------|------|\n237: | `GET` | `/auth/me` | Authenticated |\n238: \n239: **Description:** Returns the currently authenticated user's profile.\n240: \n241: **Success Response** `200 OK`:\n242: ```json\n243: {\n244:   \"success\": true,\n245:   \"statusCode\": 200,\n246:   \"message\": \"User retrieved successfully\",\n247:   \"data\": {\n248:     \"id\": \"uuid\",\n249:     \"name\": \"string\",\n250:     \"email\": \"string\",\n251:     \"phone\": \"string | null\",\n252:     \"role\": \"renter | admin\",\n253:     \"status\": \"active | suspended\",\n254:     \"emailVerifiedAt\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp | null\",\n255:     \"createdAt\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\",\n256:     \"updatedAt\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\"\n257:   },\n258:   \"timestamp\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\",\n259:   \"path\": \"/api/auth/me\"\n260: }\n261: ```\n262: \n263: **Error Responses:**\n264: - `401` — Not authenticated\n265: \n266: ---\n267: \n268: ### Profile\n269: \n270: ---\n271: \n272: #### Get Profile\n273: \n274: | Method | Path | Auth |\n275: |--------|------|------|\n276: | `GET` | `/profile` | Authenticated |\n277: \n278: **Description:** Returns the authenticated user's profile details.\n279: \n280: **Success Response** `200 OK`:\n281: ```json\n282: {\n283:   \"success\": true,\n284:   \"statusCode\": 200,\n285:   \"message\": \"Profile retrieved successfully\",\n286:   \"data\": {\n287:     \"id\": \"uuid\",\n288:     \"name\": \"string\",\n289:     \"email\": \"string\",\n290:     \"phone\": \"string | null\",\n291:     \"role\": \"renter | admin\",\n292:     \"status\": \"active | suspended\",\n293:     \"emailVerifiedAt\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp | null\",\n294:     \"createdAt\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\",\n295:     \"updatedAt\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\"\n296:   },\n297:   \"timestamp\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\",\n298:   \"path\": \"/api/profile\"\n299: }\n300: ```\n301: \n302: **Error Responses:**\n303: - `401` — Not authenticated\n304: \n305: ---\n306: \n307: #### Update Profile\n308: \n309: | Method | Path | Auth |\n310: |--------|------|------|\n311: | `PATCH` | `/profile` | Authenticated |\n312: \n313: **Description:** Updates the authenticated user's profile fields.\n314: \n315: **Request Body:**\n316: ```json\n317: {\n318:   \"name\": \"string (2–100 chars, optional)\",\n319:   \"phone\": \"string (max 20 chars, optional)\"\n320: }\n321: ```\n322: \n323: **Success Response** `200 OK`:\n324: ```json\n325: {\n326:   \"success\": true,\n327:   \"statusCode\": 200,\n328:   \"message\": \"Profile updated successfully\",\n329:   \"data\": {\n330:     \"id\": \"uuid\",\n331:     \"name\": \"string\",\n332:     \"email\": \"string\",\n333:     \"phone\": \"string | null\",\n334:     \"role\": \"renter | admin\",\n335:     \"status\": \"active | suspended\",\n336:     \"createdAt\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\",\n337:     \"updatedAt\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\"\n338:   },\n339:   \"timestamp\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\",\n340:   \"path\": \"/api/profile\"\n341: }\n342: ```\n343: \n344: **Error Responses:**\n345: - `400` — Validation failed\n346: - `401` — Not authenticated\n347: \n348: ---\n349: \n350: ### Properties\n351: \n352: ---\n353: \n354: #### Search Properties\n355: \n356: | Method | Path | Auth |\n357: |--------|------|------|\n358: | `GET` | `/properties` | Public |\n359: \n360: **Description:** Search and filter rental property listings. Returns paginated results. Only returns non-archived (non-soft-deleted) properties.\n361: \n362: **Query Parameters:**\n363: | Param | Type | Required | Description |\n364: |-------|------|----------|-------------|\n365: | `search` | string | no | Full-text search across title, description, city, state |\n366: | `propertyType` | enum | no | Filter: `apartment`, `house`, `condo`, `townhouse`, `studio` |\n367: | `minPrice` | number | no | Minimum monthly rent |\n368: | `maxPrice` | number | no | Maximum monthly rent |\n369: | `bedrooms` | number | no | Minimum number of bedrooms |\n370: | `bathrooms` | number | no | Minimum number of bathrooms |\n371: | `city` | string | no | Filter by city |\n372: | `state` | string | no | Filter by state |\n373: | `latitude` | number | no | Latitude for geolocation search |\n374: | `longitude` | number | no | Longitude for geolocation search |\n375: | `radius` | number | no | Search radius in miles (requires lat/lon) |\n376: | `sortBy` | enum | no | `price_asc`, `price_desc`, `newest`, `oldest` |\n377: | `page` | number | no | Page number (default: 1) |\n378: | `limit` | number | no | Items per page (default: 20, max: 100) |\n379: \n380: **Success Response** `200 OK`:\n381: ```json\n382: {\n383:   \"success\": true,\n384:   \"statusCode\": 200,\n385:   \"message\": \"Properties retrieved successfully\",\n386:   \"data\": {\n387:     \"items\": [\n388:       {\n389:         \"id\": \"uuid\",\n390:         \"title\": \"string\",\n391:         \"description\": \"string\",\n392:         \"price\": 2500.00,\n393:         \"bedrooms\": 2,\n394:         \"bathrooms\": 1,\n395:         \"squareFeet\": 950,\n396:         \"propertyType\": \"apartment\",\n397:         \"address\": {\n398:           \"street\": \"string\",\n399:           \"city\": \"string\",\n400:           \"state\": \"string\",\n401:           \"zipCode\": \"string\",\n402:           \"latitude\": 40.7127753,\n403:           \"longitude\": -74.0059728\n404:         },\n405:         \"availableFrom\": \"2026-06-01\",\n406:         \"primaryPhoto\": \"string (URL) | null\",\n407:         \"amenities\": [\n408:           { \"id\": \"uuid\", \"name\": \"Parking\", \"icon\": \"parking\" }\n409:         ],\n410:         \"createdAt\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\"\n411:       }\n412:     ],\n413:     \"meta\": {\n414:       \"total\": 150,\n415:       \"page\": 1,\n416:       \"limit\": 20,\n417:       \"totalPages\": 8\n418:     }\n419:   },\n420:   \"timestamp\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\",\n421:   \"path\": \"/api/properties\"\n422: }\n423: ```\n424: \n425: **Error Responses:**\n426: - `400` — Invalid query parameters\n427: \n428: ---\n429: \n430: #### Get Property Detail\n431: \n432: | Method | Path | Auth |\n433: |--------|------|------|\n434: | `GET` | `/properties/:id` | Public |\n435: \n436: **Description:** Returns full property details including all photos, amenities, and address.\n437: \n438: **Success Response** `200 OK`:\n439: ```json\n440: {\n441:   \"success\": true,\n442:   \"statusCode\": 200,\n443:   \"message\": \"Property retrieved successfully\",\n444:   \"data\": {\n445:     \"id\": \"uuid\",\n446:     \"title\": \"string\",\n447:     \"description\": \"string\",\n448:     \"price\": 2500.00,\n449:     \"bedrooms\": 2,\n450:     \"bathrooms\": 1,\n451:     \"squareFeet\": 950,\n452:     \"propertyType\": \"apartment\",\n453:     \"address\": {\n454:       \"street\": \"string\",\n455:       \"city\": \"string\",\n456:       \"state\": \"string\",\n457:       \"zipCode\": \"string\",\n458:       \"latitude\": 40.7127753,\n459:       \"longitude\": -74.0059728\n460:     },\n461:     \"availableFrom\": \"2026-06-01\",\n462:     \"photos\": [\n463:       {\n464:         \"id\": \"uuid\",\n465:         \"url\": \"string\",\n466:         \"isPrimary\": true,\n467:         \"sortOrder\": 0\n468:       }\n469:     ],\n470:     \"amenities\": [\n471:       { \"id\": \"uuid\", \"name\": \"Parking\", \"icon\": \"parking\" }\n472:     ],\n473:     \"isFavorited\": false,\n474:     \"createdAt\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\",\n475:     \"updatedAt\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\"\n476:   },\n477:   \"timestamp\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\",\n478:   \"path\": \"/api/properties/uuid\"\n479: }\n480: ```\n481: \n482: **Error Responses:**\n483: - `400` — Invalid UUID format\n484: - `404` — Property not found or archived\n485: \n486: ---\n487: \n488: #### Create Property\n489: \n490: | Method | Path | Auth |\n491: |--------|------|------|\n492: | `POST` | `/properties` | Admin |\n493: \n494: **Description:** Create a new rental property listing.\n495: \n496: **Request Body:**\n497: ```json\n498: {\n499:   \"title\": \"string (5–200 chars, required)\",\n500:   \"description\": \"string (20–5000 chars, required)\",\n501:   \"price\": \"number (>0, required)\",\n502:   \"bedrooms\": \"number (>=0, required)\",\n503:   \"bathrooms\": \"number (>=0, required)\",\n504:   \"squareFeet\": \"number (>0, optional)\",\n505:   \"propertyType\": \"enum (apartment | house | condo | townhouse | studio, required)\",\n506:   \"address\": {\n507:     \"street\": \"string (required, max 200)\",\n508:     \"city\": \"string (required, max 100)\",\n509:     \"state\": \"string (required, max 100)\",\n510:     \"zipCode\": \"string (required, max 10)\",\n511:     \"latitude\": \"number (-90 to 90, optional)\",\n512:     \"longitude\": \"number (-180 to 180, optional)\"\n513:   },\n514:   \"availableFrom\": \"date string (ISO date format, optional)\",\n515:   \"amenityIds\": [\"uuid\", \"uuid\"]\n516: }\n517: ```\n518: \n519: **Success Response** `201 Created`:\n520: ```json\n521: {\n522:   \"success\": true,\n523:   \"statusCode\": 201,\n524:   \"message\": \"Property created successfully\",\n525:   \"data\": {\n526:     \"id\": \"uuid\",\n527:     \"title\": \"string\",\n528:     \"description\": \"string\",\n529:     \"price\": 2500.00,\n530:     \"bedrooms\": 2,\n531:     \"bathrooms\": 1,\n532:     \"squareFeet\": 950,\n533:     \"propertyType\": \"apartment\",\n534:     \"address\": {\n535:       \"street\": \"string\",\n536:       \"city\": \"string\",\n537:       \"state\": \"string\",\n538:       \"zipCode\": \"string\",\n539:       \"latitude\": 40.7127753,\n540:       \"longitude\": -74.0059728\n541:     },\n542:     \"availableFrom\": \"2026-06-01\",\n543:     \"amenities\": [\n544:       { \"id\": \"uuid\", \"name\": \"Parking\", \"icon\": \"parking\" }\n545:     ],\n546:     \"photos\": [],\n547:     \"createdAt\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\",\n548:     \"updatedAt\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\"\n549:   },\n550:   \"timestamp\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\",\n551:   \"path\": \"/api/properties\"\n552: }\n553: ```\n554: \n555: **Error Responses:**\n556: - `400` — Validation failed\n557: - `401` — Not authenticated\n558: - `403` — Insufficient permissions (not admin)\n559: \n560: ---\n561: \n562: #### Update Property\n563: \n564: | Method | Path | Auth |\n565: |--------|------|------|\n566: | `PATCH` | `/properties/:id` | Admin |\n567: \n568: **Description:** Update an existing property listing. Only provided fields are updated.\n569: \n570: **Request Body (all fields optional):**\n571: ```json\n572: {\n573:   \"title\": \"string (5–200 chars)\",\n574:   \"description\": \"string (20–5000 chars)\",\n575:   \"price\": \"number (>0)\",\n576:   \"bedrooms\": \"number (>=0)\",\n577:   \"bathrooms\": \"number (>=0)\",\n578:   \"squareFeet\": \"number (>0)\",\n579:   \"propertyType\": \"enum (apartment | house | condo | townhouse | studio)\",\n580:   \"address\": {\n581:     \"street\": \"string (max 200)\",\n582:     \"city\": \"string (max 100)\",\n583:     \"state\": \"string (max 100)\",\n584:     \"zipCode\": \"string (max 10)\",\n585:     \"latitude\": \"number (-90 to 90)\",\n586:     \"longitude\": \"number (-180 to 180)\"\n587:   },\n588:   \"availableFrom\": \"date string (ISO date format)\",\n589:   \"amenityIds\": [\"uuid\", \"uuid\"]\n590: }\n591: ```\n592: \n593: **Success Response** `200 OK`:\n594: ```json\n595: {\n596:   \"success\": true,\n597:   \"statusCode\": 200,\n598:   \"message\": \"Property updated successfully\",\n599:   \"data\": {\n600:     \"id\": \"uuid\",\n601:     \"title\": \"string\",\n602:     \"description\": \"string\",\n603:     \"price\": 2500.00,\n604:     \"bedrooms\": 2,\n605:     \"bathrooms\": 1,\n606:     \"squareFeet\": 950,\n607:     \"propertyType\": \"apartment\",\n608:     \"address\": {\n609:       \"street\": \"string\",\n610:       \"city\": \"string\",\n611:       \"state\": \"string\",\n612:       \"zipCode\": \"string\",\n613:       \"latitude\": 40.7127753,\n614:       \"longitude\": -74.0059728\n615:     },\n616:     \"availableFrom\": \"2026-06-01\",\n617:     \"amenities\": [\n618:       { \"id\": \"uuid\", \"name\": \"Parking\", \"icon\": \"parking\" }\n619:     ],\n620:     \"photos\": [\n621:       {\n622:         \"id\": \"uuid\",\n623:         \"url\": \"string\",\n624:         \"isPrimary\": true,\n625:         \"sortOrder\": 0\n626:       }\n627:     ],\n628:     \"createdAt\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\",\n629:     \"updatedAt\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\"\n630:   },\n631:   \"timestamp\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\",\n632:   \"path\": \"/api/properties/uuid\"\n633: }\n634: ```\n635: \n636: **Error Responses:**\n637: - `400` — Validation failed or invalid UUID\n638: - `401` — Not authenticated\n639: - `403` — Insufficient permissions (not admin)\n640: - `404` — Property not found\n641: \n642: ---\n643: \n644: #### Delete (Archive) Property\n645: \n646: | Method | Path | Auth |\n647: |--------|------|------|\n648: | `DELETE` | `/properties/:id` | Admin |\n649: \n650: **Description:** Soft-deletes (archives) a property listing. The property is removed from public search results but retained in the database.\n651: \n652: **Success Response** `200 OK`:\n653: ```json\n654: {\n655:   \"success\": true,\n656:   \"statusCode\": 200,\n657:   \"message\": \"Property archived successfully\",\n658:   \"data\": null,\n659:   \"timestamp\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\",\n660:   \"path\": \"/api/properties/uuid\"\n661: }\n662: ```\n663: \n664: **Error Responses:**\n665: - `400` — Invalid UUID format\n666: - `401` — Not authenticated\n667: - `403` — Insufficient permissions (not admin)\n668: - `404` — Property not found\n669: \n670: ---\n671: \n672: #### Upload Property Photos\n673: \n674: | Method | Path | Auth |\n675: |--------|------|------|\n676: | `POST` | `/properties/:id/photos` | Admin |\n677: \n678: **Description:** Upload one or more photos for a property. The first photo uploaded is automatically set as primary if no primary exists.\n679: \n680: **Request:** `multipart/form-data`\n681: | Field | Type | Required | Description |\n682: |-------|------|----------|-------------|\n683: | `files` | file[] | yes | Image files (max 10 per request, accepted: jpg, jpeg, png, webp; max 5MB each) |\n684: \n685: **Success Response** `201 Created`:\n686: ```json\n687: {\n688:   \"success\": true,\n689:   \"statusCode\": 201,\n690:   \"message\": \"Photos uploaded successfully\",\n691:   \"data\": [\n692:     {\n693:       \"id\": \"uuid\",\n694:       \"url\": \"string\",\n695:       \"isPrimary\": true,\n696:       \"sortOrder\": 0\n697:     }\n698:   ],\n699:   \"timestamp\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\",\n700:   \"path\": \"/api/properties/uuid/photos\"\n701: }\n702: ```\n703: \n704: **Error Responses:**\n705: - `400` — Invalid file type, file too large, or no file provided\n706: - `401` — Not authenticated\n707: - `403` — Insufficient permissions (not admin)\n708: - `404` — Property not found\n709: \n710: ---\n711: \n712: #### Delete Property Photo\n713: \n714: | Method | Path | Auth |\n715: |--------|------|------|\n716: | `DELETE` | `/properties/:id/photos/:photoId` | Admin |\n717: \n718: **Description:** Delete a specific photo from a property.\n719: \n720: **Success Response** `200 OK`:\n721: ```json\n722: {\n723:   \"success\": true,\n724:   \"statusCode\": 200,\n725:   \"message\": \"Photo deleted successfully\",\n726:   \"data\": null,\n727:   \"timestamp\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\",\n728:   \"path\": \"/api/properties/uuid/photos/uuid\"\n729: }\n730: ```\n731: \n732: **Error Responses:**\n733: - `400` — Invalid UUID format\n734: - `401` — Not authenticated\n735: - `403` — Insufficient permissions (not admin)\n736: - `404` — Property or photo not found\n737: \n738: ---\n739: \n740: #### Set Primary Photo\n741: \n742: | Method | Path | Auth |\n743: |--------|------|------|\n744: | `PATCH` | `/properties/:id/photos/:photoId/primary` | Admin |\n745: \n746: **Description:** Set a specific photo as the primary/thumbnail photo for the property. The previous primary is unset.\n747: \n748: **Success Response** `200 OK`:\n749: ```json\n750: {\n751:   \"success\": true,\n752:   \"statusCode\": 200,\n753:   \"message\": \"Primary photo updated successfully\",\n754:   \"data\": {\n755:     \"id\": \"uuid\",\n756:     \"url\": \"string\",\n757:     \"isPrimary\": true,\n758:     \"sortOrder\": 0\n759:   },\n760:   \"timestamp\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\",\n761:   \"path\": \"/api/properties/uuid/photos/uuid/primary\"\n762: }\n763: ```\n764: \n765: **Error Responses:**\n766: - `400` — Invalid UUID format\n767: - `401` — Not authenticated\n768: - `403` — Insufficient permissions (not admin)\n769: - `404` — Property or photo not found\n770: \n771: ---\n772: \n773: #### Reorder Property Photos\n774: \n775: | Method | Path | Auth |\n776: |--------|------|------|\n777: | `PATCH` | `/properties/:id/photos/reorder` | Admin |\n778: \n779: **Description:** Reorder the display order of photos for a property.\n780: \n781: **Request Body:**\n782: ```json\n783: {\n784:   \"photoIds\": [\"uuid\", \"uuid\", \"uuid\"]\n785: }\n786: ```\n787: \n788: **Success Response** `200 OK`:\n789: ```json\n790: {\n791:   \"success\": true,\n792:   \"statusCode\": 200,\n793:   \"message\": \"Photo order updated successfully\",\n794:   \"data\": [\n795:     {\n796:       \"id\": \"uuid\",\n797:       \"url\": \"string\",\n798:       \"isPrimary\": true,\n799:       \"sortOrder\": 0\n800:     },\n801:     {\n802:       \"id\": \"uuid\",\n803:       \"url\": \"string\",\n804:       \"isPrimary\": false,\n805:       \"sortOrder\": 1\n806:     }\n807:   ],\n808:   \"timestamp\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\",\n809:   \"path\": \"/api/properties/uuid/photos/reorder\"\n810: }\n811: ```\n812: \n813: **Error Responses:**\n814: - `400` — Invalid photo IDs or missing photos in array\n815: - `401` — Not authenticated\n816: - `403` — Insufficient permissions (not admin)\n817: - `404` — Property not found\n818: \n819: ---\n820: \n821: ### Favorites\n822: \n823: ---\n824: \n825: #### List Favorites\n826: \n827: | Method | Path | Auth |\n828: |--------|------|------|\n829: | `GET` | `/favorites` | Renter |\n830: \n831: **Description:** List all properties favorited by the authenticated renter. Returns paginated results.\n832: \n833: **Query Parameters:**\n834: | Param | Type | Required | Description |\n835: |-------|------|----------|-------------|\n836: | `page` | number | no | Page number (default: 1) |\n837: | `limit` | number | no | Items per page (default: 20, max: 100) |\n838: \n839: **Success Response** `200 OK`:\n840: ```json\n841: {\n842:   \"success\": true,\n843:   \"statusCode\": 200,\n844:   \"message\": \"Favorites retrieved successfully\",\n845:   \"data\": {\n846:     \"items\": [\n847:       {\n848:         \"id\": \"uuid (favorite record ID)\",\n849:         \"property\": {\n850:           \"id\": \"uuid\",\n851:           \"title\": \"string\",\n852:           \"price\": 2500.00,\n853:           \"bedrooms\": 2,\n854:           \"bathrooms\": 1,\n855:           \"propertyType\": \"apartment\",\n856:           \"address\": {\n857:             \"city\": \"string\",\n858:             \"state\": \"string\"\n859:           },\n860:           \"primaryPhoto\": \"string (URL) | null\"\n861:         },\n862:         \"createdAt\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\"\n863:       }\n864:     ],\n865:     \"meta\": {\n866:       \"total\": 12,\n867:       \"page\": 1,\n868:       \"limit\": 20,\n869:       \"totalPages\": 1\n870:     }\n871:   },\n872:   \"timestamp\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\",\n873:   \"path\": \"/api/favorites\"\n874: }\n875: ```\n876: \n877: **Error Responses:**\n878: - `401` — Not authenticated\n879: \n880: ---\n881: \n882: #### Add to Favorites\n883: \n884: | Method | Path | Auth |\n885: |--------|------|------|\n886: | `POST` | `/favorites` | Renter |\n887: \n888: **Description:** Add a property to the authenticated renter's favorites. Idempotent — adding a duplicate returns the existing record without error.\n889: \n890: **Request Body:**\n891: ```json\n892: {\n893:   \"propertyId\": \"uuid (required)\"\n894: }\n895: ```\n896: \n897: **Success Response** `201 Created`:\n898: ```json\n899: {\n900:   \"success\": true,\n901:   \"statusCode\": 201,\n902:   \"message\": \"Property added to favorites\",\n903:   \"data\": {\n904:     \"id\": \"uuid\",\n905:     \"propertyId\": \"uuid\",\n906:     \"createdAt\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\"\n907:   },\n908:   \"timestamp\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\",\n909:   \"path\": \"/api/favorites\"\n910: }\n911: ```\n912: \n913: **Error Responses:**\n914: - `400` — Invalid property ID or validation failed\n915: - `401` — Not authenticated\n916: - `404` — Property not found\n917: \n918: ---\n919: \n920: #### Remove from Favorites\n921: \n922: | Method | Path | Auth |\n923: |--------|------|------|\n924: | `DELETE` | `/favorites/:propertyId` | Renter |\n925: \n926: **Description:** Remove a property from the authenticated renter's favorites.\n927: \n928: **Success Response** `200 OK`:\n929: ```json\n930: {\n931:   \"success\": true,\n932:   \"statusCode\": 200,\n933:   \"message\": \"Property removed from favorites\",\n934:   \"data\": null,\n935:   \"timestamp\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\",\n936:   \"path\": \"/api/favorites/uuid\"\n937: }\n938: ```\n939: \n940: **Error Responses:**\n941: - `400` — Invalid UUID format\n942: - `401` — Not authenticated\n943: - `404` — Favorite not found\n944: \n945: ---\n946: \n947: ### Inquiries\n948: \n949: ---\n950: \n951: #### Submit Inquiry\n952: \n953: | Method | Path | Auth |\n954: |--------|------|------|\n955: | `POST` | `/properties/:id/inquiries` | Renter |\n956: \n957: **Description:** Submit an inquiry about a specific property. Name, email, and phone are denormalized from the authenticated user's profile at submission time.\n958: \n959: **Request Body:**\n960: ```json\n961: {\n962:   \"message\": \"string (10–2000 chars, required)\",\n963:   \"name\": \"string (optional, defaults to user's name)\",\n964:   \"email\": \"string (optional, defaults to user's email)\",\n965:   \"phone\": \"string (optional, defaults to user's phone)\"\n966: }\n967: ```\n968: \n969: **Success Response** `201 Created`:\n970: ```json\n971: {\n972:   \"success\": true,\n973:   \"statusCode\": 201,\n974:   \"message\": \"Inquiry submitted successfully\",\n975:   \"data\": {\n976:     \"id\": \"uuid\",\n977:     \"propertyId\": \"uuid\",\n978:     \"name\": \"string\",\n979:     \"email\": \"string\",\n980:     \"phone\": \"string | null\",\n981:     \"message\": \"string\",\n982:     \"status\": \"new\",\n983:     \"response\": null,\n984:     \"respondedAt\": null,\n985:     \"createdAt\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\"\n986:   },\n987:   \"timestamp\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\",\n988:   \"path\": \"/api/properties/uuid/inquiries\"\n989: }\n990: ```\n991: \n992: **Error Responses:**\n993: - `400` — Validation failed or invalid UUID\n994: - `401` — Not authenticated\n995: - `404` — Property not found\n996: \n997: ---\n998: \n999: #### List All Inquiries (Admin)\n1000: \n1001: | Method | Path | Auth |\n1002: |--------|------|------|\n1003: | `GET` | `/inquiries` | Admin |\n1004: \n1005: **Description:** Admin endpoint to view all inquiries with filtering and pagination.\n1006: \n1007: **Query Parameters:**\n1008: | Param | Type | Required | Description |\n1009: |-------|------|----------|-------------|\n1010: | `status` | enum | no | Filter: `new`, `read`, `responded` |\n1011: | `propertyId` | uuid | no | Filter by property |\n1012: | `search` | string | no | Search by name or email |\n1013: | `sortBy` | enum | no | `newest` (default), `oldest` |\n1014: | `page` | number | no | Page number (default: 1) |\n1015: | `limit` | number | no | Items per page (default: 20, max: 100) |\n1016: \n1017: **Success Response** `200 OK`:\n1018: ```json\n1019: {\n1020:   \"success\": true,\n1021:   \"statusCode\": 200,\n1022:   \"message\": \"Inquiries retrieved successfully\",\n1023:   \"data\": {\n1024:     \"items\": [\n1025:       {\n1026:         \"id\": \"uuid\",\n1027:         \"property\": {\n1028:           \"id\": \"uuid\",\n1029:           \"title\": \"string\"\n1030:         },\n1031:         \"renter\": {\n1032:           \"id\": \"uuid\",\n1033:           \"name\": \"string\",\n1034:           \"email\": \"string\"\n1035:         },\n1036:         \"name\": \"string\",\n1037:         \"email\": \"string\",\n1038:         \"phone\": \"string | null\",\n1039:         \"message\": \"string\",\n1040:         \"status\": \"new | read | responded\",\n1041:         \"response\": \"string | null\",\n1042:         \"respondedAt\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp | null\",\n1043:         \"createdAt\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\",\n1044:         \"updatedAt\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\"\n1045:       }\n1046:     ],\n1047:     \"meta\": {\n1048:       \"total\": 45,\n1049:       \"page\": 1,\n1050:       \"limit\": 20,\n1051:       \"totalPages\": 3\n1052:     }\n1053:   },\n1054:   \"timestamp\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\",\n1055:   \"path\": \"/api/inquiries\"\n1056: }\n1057: ```\n1058: \n1059: **Error Responses:**\n1060: - `401` — Not authenticated\n1061: - `403` — Insufficient permissions (not admin)\n1062: \n1063: ---\n1064: \n1065: #### Get Inquiry Detail\n1066: \n1067: | Method | Path | Auth |\n1068: |--------|------|------|\n1069: | `GET` | `/inquiries/:id` | Admin |\n1070: \n1071: **Description:** Get full details of a single inquiry.\n1072: \n1073: **Success Response** `200 OK`:\n1074: ```json\n1075: {\n1076:   \"success\": true,\n1077:   \"statusCode\": 200,\n1078:   \"message\": \"Inquiry retrieved successfully\",\n1079:   \"data\": {\n1080:     \"id\": \"uuid\",\n1081:     \"property\": {\n1082:       \"id\": \"uuid\",\n1083:       \"title\": \"string\"\n1084:     },\n1085:     \"renter\": {\n1086:       \"id\": \"uuid\",\n1087:       \"name\": \"string\",\n1088:       \"email\": \"string\"\n1089:     },\n1090:     \"name\": \"string\",\n1091:     \"email\": \"string\",\n1092:     \"phone\": \"string | null\",\n1093:     \"message\": \"string\",\n1094:     \"status\": \"new | read | responded\",\n1095:     \"response\": \"string | null\",\n1096:     \"respondedAt\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp | null\",\n1097:     \"createdAt\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\",\n1098:     \"updatedAt\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\"\n1099:   },\n1100:   \"timestamp\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\",\n1101:   \"path\": \"/api/inquiries/uuid\"\n1102: }\n1103: ```\n1104: \n1105: **Error Responses:**\n1106: - `400` — Invalid UUID\n1107: - `401` — Not authenticated\n1108: - `403` — Insufficient permissions (not admin)\n1109: - `404` — Inquiry not found\n1110: \n1111: ---\n1112: \n1113: #### Mark Inquiry as Read\n1114: \n1115: | Method | Path | Auth |\n1116: |--------|------|------|\n1117: | `PATCH` | `/inquiries/:id/read` | Admin |\n1118: \n1119: **Description:** Mark an inquiry as read. Only applicable to inquiries with `new` status.\n1120: \n1121: **Request Body:** none\n1122: \n1123: **Success Response** `200 OK`:\n1124: ```json\n1125: {\n1126:   \"success\": true,\n1127:   \"statusCode\": 200,\n1128:   \"message\": \"Inquiry marked as read\",\n1129:   \"data\": {\n1130:     \"id\": \"uuid\",\n1131:     \"status\": \"read\",\n1132:     \"updatedAt\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\"\n1133:   },\n1134:   \"timestamp\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\",\n1135:   \"path\": \"/api/inquiries/uuid/read\"\n1136: }\n1137: ```\n1138: \n1139: **Error Responses:**\n1140: - `400` — Invalid UUID or inquiry already read/responded\n1141: - `401` — Not authenticated\n1142: - `403` — Insufficient permissions (not admin)\n1143: - `404` — Inquiry not found\n1144: \n1145: ---\n1146: \n1147: #### Respond to Inquiry\n1148: \n1149: | Method | Path | Auth |\n1150: |--------|------|------|\n1151: | `POST` | `/inquiries/:id/respond` | Admin |\n1152: \n1153: **Description:** Admin responds to an inquiry. Sets status to `responded` and records the response and timestamp.\n1154: \n1155: **Request Body:**\n1156: ```json\n1157: {\n1158:   \"response\": \"string (10–5000 chars, required)\"\n1159: }\n1160: ```\n1161: \n1162: **Success Response** `200 OK`:\n1163: ```json\n1164: {\n1165:   \"success\": true,\n1166:   \"statusCode\": 200,\n1167:   \"message\": \"Response sent successfully\",\n1168:   \"data\": {\n1169:     \"id\": \"uuid\",\n1170:     \"status\": \"responded\",\n1171:     \"response\": \"string\",\n1172:     \"respondedAt\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\",\n1173:     \"updatedAt\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\"\n1174:   },\n1175:   \"timestamp\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\",\n1176:   \"path\": \"/api/inquiries/uuid/respond\"\n1177: }\n1178: ```\n1179: \n1180: **Error Responses:**\n1181: - `400` — Validation failed or invalid UUID\n1182: - `401` — Not authenticated\n1183: - `403` — Insufficient permissions (not admin)\n1184: - `404` — Inquiry not found\n1185: \n1186: ---\n1187: \n1188: ### Amenities\n1189: \n1190: ---\n1191: \n1192: #### List Amenities\n1193: \n1194: | Method | Path | Auth |\n1195: |--------|------|------|\n1196: | `GET` | `/amenities` | Public |\n1197: \n1198: **Description:** List all available amenities. Used for property creation/editing forms and property detail display.\n1199: \n1200: **Success Response** `200 OK`:\n1201: ```json\n1202: {\n1203:   \"success\": true,\n1204:   \"statusCode\": 200,\n1205:   \"message\": \"Amenities retrieved successfully\",\n1206:   \"data\": [\n1207:     {\n1208:       \"id\": \"uuid\",\n1209:       \"name\": \"Parking\",\n1210:       \"icon\": \"parking\"\n1211:     },\n1212:     {\n1213:       \"id\": \"uuid\",\n1214:       \"name\": \"Gym\",\n1215:       \"icon\": \"gym\"\n1216:     }\n1217:   ],\n1218:   \"timestamp\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\",\n1219:   \"path\": \"/api/amenities\"\n1220: }\n1221: ```\n1222: \n1223: **Error Responses:** none (always returns array, empty if no amenities exist)\n1224: \n1225: ---\n1226: \n1227: #### Create Amenity\n1228: \n1229: | Method | Path | Auth |\n1230: |--------|------|------|\n1231: | `POST` | `/amenities` | Admin |\n1232: \n1233: **Description:** Create a new amenity option.\n1234: \n1235: **Request Body:**\n1236: ```json\n1237: {\n1238:   \"name\": \"string (1–50 chars, required, unique)\",\n1239:   \"icon\": \"string (1–50 chars, required)\"\n1240: }\n1241: ```\n1242: \n1243: **Success Response** `201 Created`:\n1244: ```json\n1245: {\n1246:   \"success\": true,\n1247:   \"statusCode\": 201,\n1248:   \"message\": \"Amenity created successfully\",\n1249:   \"data\": {\n1250:     \"id\": \"uuid\",\n1251:     \"name\": \"Parking\",\n1252:     \"icon\": \"parking\",\n1253:     \"createdAt\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\",\n1254:     \"updatedAt\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\"\n1255:   },\n1256:   \"timestamp\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\",\n1257:   \"path\": \"/api/amenities\"\n1258: }\n1259: ```\n1260: \n1261: **Error Responses:**\n1262: - `400` — Validation failed\n1263: - `401` — Not authenticated\n1264: - `403` — Insufficient permissions (not admin)\n1265: - `409` — Amenity name already exists\n1266: \n1267: ---\n1268: \n1269: #### Update Amenity\n1270: \n1271: | Method | Path | Auth |\n1272: |--------|------|------|\n1273: | `PATCH` | `/amenities/:id` | Admin |\n1274: \n1275: **Description:** Update an existing amenity name or icon.\n1276: \n1277: **Request Body (all fields optional):**\n1278: ```json\n1279: {\n1280:   \"name\": \"string (1–50 chars)\",\n1281:   \"icon\": \"string (1–50 chars)\"\n1282: }\n1283: ```\n1284: \n1285: **Success Response** `200 OK`:\n1286: ```json\n1287: {\n1288:   \"success\": true,\n1289:   \"statusCode\": 200,\n1290:   \"message\": \"Amenity updated successfully\",\n1291:   \"data\": {\n1292:     \"id\": \"uuid\",\n1293:     \"name\": \"Parking\",\n1294:     \"icon\": \"parking\",\n1295:     \"updatedAt\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\"\n1296:   },\n1297:   \"timestamp\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\",\n1298:   \"path\": \"/api/amenities/uuid\"\n1299: }\n1300: ```\n1301: \n1302: **Error Responses:**\n1303: - `400` — Validation failed or invalid UUID\n1304: - `401` — Not authenticated\n1305: - `403` — Insufficient permissions (not admin)\n1306: - `404` — Amenity not found\n1307: - `409` — Amenity name already exists\n1308: \n1309: ---\n1310: \n1311: #### Delete Amenity\n1312: \n1313: | Method | Path | Auth |\n1314: |--------|------|------|\n1315: | `DELETE` | `/amenities/:id` | Admin |\n1316: \n1317: **Description:** Soft-delete an amenity. Properties already associated retain the amenity but it no longer appears in the amenity list for new associations.\n1318: \n1319: **Success Response** `200 OK`:\n1320: ```json\n1321: {\n1322:   \"success\": true,\n1323:   \"statusCode\": 200,\n1324:   \"message\": \"Amenity deleted successfully\",\n1325:   \"data\": null,\n1326:   \"timestamp\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\",\n1327:   \"path\": \"/api/amenities/uuid\"\n1328: }\n1329: ```\n1330: \n1331: **Error Responses:**\n1332: - `400` — Invalid UUID\n1333: - `401` — Not authenticated\n1334: - `403` — Insufficient permissions (not admin)\n1335: - `404` — Amenity not found\n1336: \n1337: ---\n1338: \n1339: ### Admin Dashboard\n1340: \n1341: ---\n1342: \n1343: #### Dashboard Statistics\n1344: \n1345: | Method | Path | Auth |\n1346: |--------|------|------|\n1347: | `GET` | `/admin/dashboard` | Admin |\n1348: \n1349: **Description:** Returns aggregate statistics for the admin dashboard overview.\n1350: \n1351: **Success Response** `200 OK`:\n1352: ```json\n1353: {\n1354:   \"success\": true,\n1355:   \"statusCode\": 200,\n1356:   \"message\": \"Dashboard statistics retrieved\",\n1357:   \"data\": {\n1358:     \"totalProperties\": 150,\n1359:     \"totalInquiries\": 45,\n1360:     \"newInquiries\": 12,\n1361:     \"totalUsers\": 520,\n1362:     \"recentInquiries\": [\n1363:       {\n1364:         \"id\": \"uuid\",\n1365:         \"name\": \"string\",\n1366:         \"email\": \"string\",\n1367:         \"propertyTitle\": \"string\",\n1368:         \"status\": \"new\",\n1369:         \"createdAt\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\"\n1370:       }\n1371:     ],\n1372:     \"recentProperties\": [\n1373:       {\n1374:         \"id\": \"uuid\",\n1375:         \"title\": \"string\",\n1376:         \"price\": 2500.00,\n1377:         \"propertyType\": \"apartment\",\n1378:         \"createdAt\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\"\n1379:       }\n1380:     ]\n1381:   },\n1382:   \"timestamp\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\",\n1383:   \"path\": \"/api/admin/dashboard\"\n1384: }\n1385: ```\n1386: \n1387: **Error Responses:**\n1388: - `401` — Not authenticated\n1389: - `403` — Insufficient permissions (not admin)\n1390: \n1391: ---\n1392: \n1393: ### Admin User Management\n1394: \n1395: ---\n1396: \n1397: #### List Users\n1398: \n1399: | Method | Path | Auth |\n1400: |--------|------|------|\n1401: | `GET` | `/admin/users` | Admin |\n1402: \n1403: **Description:** List all registered users with filtering and pagination.\n1404: \n1405: **Query Parameters:**\n1406: | Param | Type | Required | Description |\n1407: |-------|------|----------|-------------|\n1408: | `role` | enum | no | Filter: `renter`, `admin` |\n1409: | `status` | enum | no | Filter: `active`, `suspended` |\n1410: | `search` | string | no | Search by name or email |\n1411: | `sortBy` | enum | no | `newest` (default), `oldest`, `name_asc`, `name_desc` |\n1412: | `page` | number | no | Page number (default: 1) |\n1413: | `limit` | number | no | Items per page (default: 20, max: 100) |\n1414: \n1415: **Success Response** `200 OK`:\n1416: ```json\n1417: {\n1418:   \"success\": true,\n1419:   \"statusCode\": 200,\n1420:   \"message\": \"Users retrieved successfully\",\n1421:   \"data\": {\n1422:     \"items\": [\n1423:       {\n1424:         \"id\": \"uuid\",\n1425:         \"name\": \"string\",\n1426:         \"email\": \"string\",\n1427:         \"phone\": \"string | null\",\n1428:         \"role\": \"renter\",\n1429:         \"status\": \"active\",\n1430:         \"emailVerifiedAt\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp | null\",\n1431:         \"createdAt\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\"\n1432:       }\n1433:     ],\n1434:     \"meta\": {\n1435:       \"total\": 520,\n1436:       \"page\": 1,\n1437:       \"limit\": 20,\n1438:       \"totalPages\": 26\n1439:     }\n1440:   },\n1441:   \"timestamp\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\",\n1442:   \"path\": \"/api/admin/users\"\n1443: }\n1444: ```\n1445: \n1446: **Error Responses:**\n1447: - `401` — Not authenticated\n1448: - `403` — Insufficient permissions (not admin)\n1449: \n1450: ---\n1451: \n1452: #### Get User Detail\n1453: \n1454: | Method | Path | Auth |\n1455: |--------|------|------|\n1456: | `GET` | `/admin/users/:id` | Admin |\n1457: \n1458: **Description:** Get full details of a specific user, including activity summary.\n1459: \n1460: **Success Response** `200 OK`:\n1461: ```json\n1462: {\n1463:   \"success\": true,\n1464:   \"statusCode\": 200,\n1465:   \"message\": \"User retrieved successfully\",\n1466:   \"data\": {\n1467:     \"id\": \"uuid\",\n1468:     \"name\": \"string\",\n1469:     \"email\": \"string\",\n1470:     \"phone\": \"string | null\",\n1471:     \"role\": \"renter | admin\",\n1472:     \"status\": \"active | suspended\",\n1473:     \"emailVerifiedAt\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp | null\",\n1474:     \"activity\": {\n1475:       \"totalFavorites\": 5,\n1476:       \"totalInquiries\": 3,\n1477:       \"lastLoginAt\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp | null\"\n1478:     },\n1479:     \"createdAt\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\",\n1480:     \"updatedAt\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\"\n1481:   },\n1482:   \"timestamp\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\",\n1483:   \"path\": \"/api/admin/users/uuid\"\n1484: }\n1485: ```\n1486: \n1487: **Error Responses:**\n1488: - `400` — Invalid UUID\n1489: - `401` — Not authenticated\n1490: - `403` — Insufficient permissions (not admin)\n1491: - `404` — User not found\n1492: \n1493: ---\n1494: \n1495: #### Update User Status\n1496: \n1497: | Method | Path | Auth |\n1498: |--------|------|------|\n1499: | `PATCH` | `/admin/users/:id/status` | Admin |\n1500: \n1501: **Description:** Suspend or reactivate a user account. Admins cannot suspend their own account.\n1502: \n1503: **Request Body:**\n1504: ```json\n1505: {\n1506:   \"status\": \"enum (active | suspended, required)\"\n1507: }\n1508: ```\n1509: \n1510: **Success Response** `200 OK`:\n1511: ```json\n1512: {\n1513:   \"success\": true,\n1514:   \"statusCode\": 200,\n1515:   \"message\": \"User status updated to 'suspended'\",\n1516:   \"data\": {\n1517:     \"id\": \"uuid\",\n1518:     \"name\": \"string\",\n1519:     \"email\": \"string\",\n1520:     \"status\": \"suspended\",\n1521:     \"updatedAt\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\"\n1522:   },\n1523:   \"timestamp\": \"ISO 8601 timestamp\",\n1524:   \"path\": \"/api/admin/users/uuid/status\"\n1525: }\n1526: ```\n1527: \n1528: **Error Responses:**\n1529: - `400` — Invalid status value or cannot suspend own account\n1530: - `401` — Not authenticated\n1531: - `403` — Insufficient permissions (not admin)\n1532: - `404` — User not found\n1533: \n1534: ---\n1535: \n1536: ## Standard Response Format\n1537: \n1538: All API responses follow this consistent envelope structure:\n1539: \n1540: ```json\n1541: {\n1542:   \"success\": true,\n1543:   \"statusCode\": 200,\n1544:   \"message\": \"Human-readable message\",\n1545:   \"data\": { ... } | [ ... ] | null,\n1546:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-19T12:00:00.000Z\",\n1547:   \"path\": \"/api/endpoint\"\n1548: }\n1549: ```\n1550: \n1551: ### Paginated Responses\n1552: \n1553: List endpoints return paginated data in this shape:\n1554: \n1555: ```json\n1556: {\n1557:   \"success\": true,\n1558:   \"statusCode\": 200,\n1559:   \"message\": \"...\",\n1560:   \"data\": {\n1561:     \"items\": [ ... ],\n1562:     \"meta\": {\n1563:       \"total\": 150,\n1564:       \"page\": 1,\n1565:       \"limit\": 20,\n1566:       \"totalPages\": 8\n1567:     }\n1568:   },\n1569:   \"timestamp\": \"...\",\n1570:   \"path\": \"/api/...\"\n1571: }\n1572: ```\n1573: \n1574: ### Error Responses\n1575: \n1576: ```json\n1577: {\n1578:   \"success\": false,\n1579:   \"statusCode\": 400,\n1580:   \"message\": \"Validation failed\",\n1581:   \"error\": \"Bad Request\",\n1582:   \"errors\": [\n1583:     { \"field\": \"email\", \"message\": \"email must be a valid email address\" }\n1584:   ],\n1585:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-19T12:00:00.000Z\",\n1586:   \"path\": \"/api/endpoint\"\n1587: }\n1588: ```\n1589: \n1590: ---\n1591: \n1592: ## Authentication\n1593: \n1594: All endpoints except those marked **Public** require authentication via JWT access token stored in an httpOnly cookie (`access_token`).\n1595: \n1596: - **Public endpoints** can be accessed without authentication\n1597: - **Authenticated** endpoints require a valid access token (any role)\n1598: - **Renter** endpoints require authentication + `renter` role\n1599: - **Admin** endpoints require authentication + `admin` role\n1600: \n1601: Rate limiting is applied to auth endpoints: login, register, forgot-password, reset-password (default: 10 requests per 60 seconds).\n1602: \n1603: ---\n1604: \n1605: ## HTTP Status Codes Summary\n1606: \n1607: | Code | Meaning |\n1608: |------|---------|\n1609: | 200 | OK — Success (read, update, delete, action) |\n1610: | 201 | Created — Resource created successfully |\n1611: | 400 | Bad Request — Validation failed, invalid input |\n1612: | 401 | Unauthorized — Missing or invalid access token |\n1613: | 403 | Forbidden — Insufficient role permissions |\n1614: | 404 | Not Found — Resource does not exist or is soft-deleted |\n1615: | 409 | Conflict — Duplicate resource (e.g., email, amenity name) |\n1616: | 413 | Payload Too Large — File upload exceeds size limit |\n1617: | 429 | Too Many Requests — Rate limit exceeded |\n1618: \n1619: ---\n1620: \n1621: *Generated: 2026-05-19 | Source: PROJECT_KNOWLEDGE.md + PROJECT_DATABASE.md*\n\n(End of file - total 1621 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# PROJECT_API\n\nNestFind API Contract — canonical reference for all API endpoints.\n\n**Base URL:** `http://localhost:3000/api`\n\n---\n\n## Endpoints\n\n---\n\n### Authentication\n\n---\n\n#### Register\n\n| Method | Path | Auth |\n|--------|------|------|","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".claude-project/nestfind/docs/PROJECT_API.md","time":{"start":1779187297924,"end":1779187298197}},"id":"prt_e3fd3a994001co92rLdx5FqY4i","sessionID":"ses_1c02c7df7ffeSj5NTT2zeCGmCe","messageID":"msg_e3fd3868d001ZEdV2P42jpJWVb"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779187299916,"sessionID":"ses_1c02c7df7ffeSj5NTT2zeCGmCe","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_01_JT09VYIPm6PRHozhQtIP8643","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude-project/nestfind/docs/PROJECT_KNOWLEDGE.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude-project/nestfind/docs/PROJECT_KNOWLEDGE.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # PROJECT_KNOWLEDGE\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: ### Application Purpose\n6: \n7: NestFind is a streamlined rental property listing platform that connects renters with available properties. The platform focuses exclusively on rentals, providing a clean and efficient browsing experience where renters can search, filter, view details, save favorites, and submit inquiries to property managers. An accompanying admin dashboard enables administrators to manage property listings, respond to inquiries, and oversee user accounts.\n8: \n9: The platform targets two primary user groups: Renters who browse and discover rental properties, and Administrators who manage the listings and respond to renter inquiries. NestFind integrates with Google Maps for property location display.\n10: \n11: ### Technology Stack\n12: \n13: | Layer | Technology |\n14: |-------|------------|\n15: | Backend | NestJS 11, TypeScript 5.7+ |\n16: | Frontend | React 19 with React Router 7 (framework mode) |\n17: | Database | PostgreSQL 16 |\n18: | ORM | TypeORM 0.3.x |\n19: | Authentication | JWT via httpOnly cookies (Access: 1h, Refresh: 7d) |\n20: | API Documentation | Swagger/OpenAPI |\n21: | Validation | class-validator (backend), Zod (frontend) |\n22: | Frontend State | Redux Toolkit with createAsyncThunk |\n23: | Styling | Tailwind CSS 4, Shadcn/UI |\n24: | Maps | Google Maps API |\n25: | Deployment | Docker |\n26: \n27: ### Domain\n28: \n29: `nestfind.com` — web application\n30: \n31: ---\n32: \n33: ## User Roles\n34: \n35: | Role | Description | Permissions |\n36: |------|-------------|-------------|\n37: | **Renter** | Browses rental property listings, views detailed property information, saves properties to favorites, and submits inquiries to property managers. | `browse_properties`, `view_property_details`, `save_favorites`, `submit_inquiries` |\n38: | **Admin** | Has full system access to manage property listings (CRUD), manage user accounts, view and respond to inquiries from renters. | `manage_properties`, `manage_users`, `view_inquiries`, `respond_to_inquiries` |\n39: | **Guest** | Unauthenticated visitor who can browse public property listings and view property details. Must register/login to save favorites or submit inquiries. | `browse_properties`, `view_property_details` |\n40: \n41: ### Authentication & Authorization\n42: \n43: - **JWT via httpOnly cookies**: Access token (1 hour) + Refresh token (7 days). Cookies configured with `httpOnly: true, secure: true, sameSite: 'strict'`. Tokens are never stored in localStorage.\n44: - **Role-based access control (RBAC)**: Guards at the route/endpoint level enforce role-specific permissions via `JwtAuthGuard` + `RolesGuard`.\n45: - **Guest access**: Public endpoints for browsing and viewing properties are marked with `@Public()` decorator; all other endpoints require authentication.\n46: - **Admin assignment**: Admin accounts are created by existing admins or via database seeding. Self-registration defaults to Renter role.\n47: \n48: ---\n49: \n50: ## Core Features\n51: \n52: ### Common (All Users)\n53: \n54: - **Authentication**\n55:   - User login with email + password\n56:   - JWT access token (1h) and refresh token (7d) via httpOnly cookies\n57:   - Token refresh mechanism with rotation\n58:   - Logout clears cookies\n59: \n60: - **Registration**\n61:   - Self-service sign-up with name, email, password, phone (optional)\n62:   - Default role assignment: Renter\n63:   - Email verification (optional, configurable)\n64: \n65: - **Password Reset**\n66:   - Forgot password flow via email\n67:   - Secure reset token with expiration\n68: \n69: ### Renter Features\n70: \n71: 1. **Property Search**\n72:    - Search by location (text input or current geolocation)\n73:    - Real-time filtering by price range, number of bedrooms, property type\n74:    - Results displayed as property cards with thumbnail, price, and key details\n75:    - Pagination or infinite scroll for large result sets\n76: \n77: 2. **Property Detail View**\n78:    - Full property page with photo gallery, amenities list, description, and floor plan\n79:    - Embedded Google Map showing property location\n80:    - Save to favorites (toggle)\n81:    - Contact / Submit Inquiry button\n82: \n83: 3. **Favorites Management**\n84:    - View all saved/favorited properties\n85:    - Remove properties from favorites\n86:    - Quick access from navigation\n87: \n88: 4. **Submit Inquiry**\n89:    - Contact form on property detail page (name, email, phone, message)\n90:    - Form validation before submission\n91:    - Confirmation message shown to renter\n92:    - Admin notified of new inquiry\n93: \n94: ### Admin Features\n95: \n96: 1. **Admin Dashboard**\n97:    - Overview statistics: total properties, total inquiries, recent activity\n98:    - Quick links to property management and inquiry management\n99: \n100: 2. **Property Management (CRUD)**\n101:    - List all properties with search, filter, and pagination\n102:    - Add new property with details: title, description, price, bedrooms, bathrooms, property type, address, amenities, photos (multi-upload)\n103:    - Edit existing property information\n104:    - Delete or archive property listings (soft delete)\n105: \n106: 3. **Inquiry Management**\n107:    - View all inquiries with status (new, read, responded)\n108:    - Mark inquiries as read\n109:    - Respond to inquiries directly from the dashboard\n110:    - Filter by property or renter\n111: \n112: 4. **User Management**\n113:    - View list of registered renters\n114:    - View renter details and activity history\n115:    - Suspend or reactivate user accounts\n116: \n117: ---\n118: \n119: ## Functional Requirements\n120: \n121: ### Authentication\n122: \n123: - **FR-AUTH-001**: Users must authenticate with email and password to access protected features.\n124: - **FR-AUTH-002**: JWT access tokens expire after 1 hour; refresh tokens expire after 7 days.\n125: - **FR-AUTH-003**: Refresh tokens are rotated on each use (old token invalidated).\n126: - **FR-AUTH-004**: All authentication tokens are stored in httpOnly, secure, sameSite-strict cookies.\n127: - **FR-AUTH-005**: Guest users can browse properties without authentication.\n128: \n129: ### Property Search\n130: \n131: - **FR-SEARCH-001**: Renters can search properties by location text (city, neighborhood, zip code).\n132: - **FR-SEARCH-002**: Renters can use browser geolocation to find properties near their current location.\n133: - **FR-SEARCH-003**: Results support filtering by price range (min/max), number of bedrooms, and property type.\n134: - **FR-SEARCH-004**: Filters update results in real-time without full page reload.\n135: - **FR-SEARCH-005**: Each result card displays thumbnail image, price, address, bedrooms, and bathrooms.\n136: \n137: ### Property Details\n138: \n139: - **FR-DETAIL-001**: Property detail page displays full photo gallery with navigation.\n140: - **FR-DETAIL-002**: Property page includes description, amenities list, pricing, and property specifications.\n141: - **FR-DETAIL-003**: An embedded Google Map shows the property location with a pin marker.\n142: - **FR-DETAIL-004**: Authenticated renters can toggle the property as a favorite.\n143: - **FR-DETAIL-005**: A Contact/Inquiry button is prominently displayed.\n144: \n145: ### Inquiries\n146: \n147: - **FR-INQ-001**: Inquiry form collects name, email, phone (optional), and message.\n148: - **FR-INQ-002**: Form fields are validated client-side (Zod) and server-side (class-validator).\n149: - **FR-INQ-003**: On successful submission, renter sees a confirmation message.\n150: - **FR-INQ-004**: System notifies admin of new inquiries (in-dashboard notification).\n151: \n152: ### Admin: Property Management\n153: \n154: - **FR-ADM-PROP-001**: Admin can create new property listings with all required fields.\n155: - **FR-ADM-PROP-002**: Admin can upload multiple photos per property.\n156: - **FR-ADM-PROP-003**: Admin can edit all fields of an existing property.\n157: - **FR-ADM-PROP-004**: Admin can soft-delete (archive) a property listing.\n158: - **FR-ADM-PROP-005**: Property list supports search, sort, and pagination.\n159: \n160: ### Admin: Inquiry Management\n161: \n162: - **FR-ADM-INQ-001**: Admin can view all inquiries with status indicators.\n163: - **FR-ADM-INQ-002**: Admin can filter inquiries by property or renter.\n164: - **FR-ADM-INQ-003**: Admin can mark inquiries as read and respond to them.\n165: \n166: ### Admin: User Management\n167: \n168: - **FR-ADM-USER-001**: Admin can view a list of all registered renters.\n169: - **FR-ADM-USER-002**: Admin can view individual renter details and activity.\n170: - **FR-ADM-USER-003**: Admin can suspend or reactivate user accounts.\n171: \n172: ---\n173: \n174: ## Non-Functional Requirements\n175: \n176: ### Performance\n177: \n178: - **NFR-PERF-001**: Property search results must return within 500ms for typical query loads.\n179: - **NFR-PERF-002**: Image assets should be served with lazy loading and optimized formats (WebP).\n180: - **NFR-PERF-003**: API responses must use pagination for list endpoints (default: 20 items/page).\n181: \n182: ### Security\n183: \n184: - **NFR-SEC-001**: All authenticated endpoints enforce JWT validation via guards.\n185: - **NFR-SEC-002**: Passwords are hashed using bcrypt with appropriate salt rounds.\n186: - **NFR-SEC-003**: Input validation is enforced at the API boundary using class-validator/Zod.\n187: - **NFR-SEC-004**: CORS is configured to allow only the frontend origin.\n188: - **NFR-SEC-005**: Rate limiting is applied to authentication endpoints (login, register, password reset).\n189: \n190: ### Reliability\n191: \n192: - **NFR-REL-001**: Database operations use transactions for multi-step mutations.\n193: - **NFR-REL-002**: Soft delete (`deleted_at`) is used for properties and user accounts (no destructive deletes).\n194: - **NFR-REL-003**: API errors return consistent response format with appropriate HTTP status codes.\n195: \n196: ### Maintainability\n197: \n198: - **NFR-MAIN-001**: Backend follows the 4-layer architecture pattern: Controller → Service → Repository → Entity.\n199: - **NFR-MAIN-002**: All backend layers extend base classes (`BaseController`, `BaseService`, `BaseRepository`, `BaseEntity`).\n200: - **NFR-MAIN-003**: Frontend follows file organization patterns defined in `.claude/react/docs/file-organization.md`.\n201: - **NFR-MAIN-004**: All API endpoints are documented with Swagger/OpenAPI annotations.\n202: \n203: ### Compatibility\n204: \n205: - **NFR-COMP-001**: Frontend supports latest 2 versions of Chrome, Firefox, Safari, and Edge.\n206: - **NFR-COMP-002**: Application is responsive and functional on mobile, tablet, and desktop viewports.\n207: \n208: ---\n209: \n210: ## Ontology / Glossary\n211: \n212: | Term | Definition |\n213: |------|------------|\n214: | **Property** | A rental property listing with details such as title, description, price, address, bedrooms, bathrooms, property type, amenities, and photos. |\n215: | **Property Type** | The category of rental property (e.g., apartment, house, condo, townhouse, studio). |\n216: | **Listing** | A published property that is visible to renters in search results. |\n217: | **Renter** | A registered user who browses, searches, and saves properties, and submits inquiries. |\n218: | **Admin** | A system administrator with full access to manage properties, users, and inquiries. |\n219: | **Guest** | An unauthenticated visitor who can browse and view property details. |\n220: | **Inquiry** | A contact form submission from a renter about a specific property, containing name, email, phone (optional), and message. |\n221: | **Favorites** | A saved collection of properties that a renter has bookmarked for later reference. |\n222: | **Amenity** | A feature or facility available at a property (e.g., parking, laundry, gym, pool, air conditioning). |\n223: | **Soft Delete** | A record is marked as deleted (`deleted_at` timestamp) but remains in the database, allowing recovery and audit trails. |\n224: | **Archive** | A property listing that has been soft-deleted by an admin, removing it from public search results. |\n225: | **httpOnly Cookie** | A cookie that is inaccessible to client-side JavaScript, used to store JWT tokens securely. |\n226: | **Access Token** | A short-lived JWT (1 hour) that authorizes API requests. |\n227: | **Refresh Token** | A longer-lived JWT (7 days) used to obtain new access tokens without re-authentication. |\n228: | **RBAC** | Role-Based Access Control — restricts system access based on user roles (Renter, Admin). |\n229: | **JwtAuthGuard** | A NestJS guard that validates JWT from httpOnly cookies on protected routes. |\n230: | **RolesGuard** | A NestJS guard that checks user role permissions for accessing specific endpoints. |\n231: | **BaseController** | A base class providing automatic CRUD endpoints for controllers that extend it. |\n232: | **BaseService** | A base class providing automatic CRUD business logic for services that extend it. |\n233: | **BaseRepository** | A base class providing automatic TypeORM CRUD operations for repositories that extend it. |\n234: | **BaseEntity** | A base class providing UUID primary key, timestamps (`createdAt`, `updatedAt`), and soft delete (`deletedAt`) for all entities. |\n235: | **createAsyncThunk** | Redux Toolkit utility for creating async thunk actions for API calls in the frontend. |\n236: | **React Router 7 (Framework Mode)** | The routing system used by the frontend, where routes are defined declaratively using `route()`, `layout()`, and `index()` from `@react-router/dev/routes`. |\n237: \n238: ---\n239: \n240: ## Architecture Overview\n241: \n242: ### Backend: Four-Layer Architecture\n243: \n244: ```\n245: HTTP Request\n246:     ↓\n247: Controller  (extends BaseController)  — HTTP handling, validation, Swagger docs\n248:     ↓\n249: Service     (extends BaseService)     — Business logic, rules enforcement\n250:     ↓\n251: Repository  (extends BaseRepository)  — Data access, TypeORM queries\n252:     ↓\n253: Entity      (extends BaseEntity)      — Database schema (UUID PK, timestamps, soft delete)\n254:     ↓\n255: PostgreSQL + TypeORM\n256: ```\n257: \n258: ### Frontend Architecture\n259: \n260: - **Routing**: React Router 7 framework mode with `routes.ts` defining `route()`, `layout()`, `index()` patterns\n261: - **State Management**: Redux Toolkit with `createAsyncThunk` for API data fetching; Redux slices per domain feature\n262: - **Forms**: React Hook Form + Zod validation following shadcn/ui patterns\n263: - **Auth**: JWT httpOnly cookies with AuthContext, GuestGuard, and AuthGuard components\n264: - **Source Directory**: `app/` (not `src/`), imports use `~/` alias\n265: - **Styling**: Tailwind CSS 4 + Shadcn/UI component library\n266: \n267: ### Directory Structure\n268: \n269: ```\n270: nestfind/\n271: ├── backend/\n272: │   ├── src/\n273: │   │   ├── core/              # Base classes, guards, decorators, filters\n274: │   │   │   ├── base/          # BaseEntity, BaseRepository, BaseService, BaseController\n275: │   │   │   ├── decorators/    # @Public(), @Roles(), @CurrentUser()\n276: │   │   │   ├── guards/        # JwtAuthGuard, RolesGuard\n277: │   │   │   ├── filters/       # HttpExceptionFilter\n278: │   │   │   ├── interceptors/  # TransformInterceptor, LoggingInterceptor\n279: │   │   │   └── pipes/         # ValidationPipe\n280: │   │   ├── modules/           # Feature modules (entity, repo, service, controller, module)\n281: │   │   ├── infrastructure/    # External services (mail, s3, token)\n282: │   │   └── database/          # Migrations, seeds\n283: │   └── test/                  # E2E tests\n284: ├── frontend/\n285: │   └── app/                   # Source directory\n286: │       ├── components/        # ui/, atoms/, modals/, shared/, layouts/, guards/\n287: │       ├── pages/             # Route pages\n288: │       ├── services/          # httpService.ts, httpMethods/, httpServices/\n289: │       ├── redux/             # features/, store/\n290: │       ├── types/             # .d.ts per domain\n291: │       ├── enums/             # Synced from backend\n292: │       ├── contexts/          # AuthContext\n293: │       ├── hooks/             # Custom hooks\n294: │       ├── lib/               # cn() utility\n295: │       ├── utils/             # errorHandler, validations/\n296: │       └── styles/            # Tailwind + theme variables\n297: └── docker-compose.yml\n298: ```\n299: \n300: ### API Base URLs\n301: \n302: | Environment | URL |\n303: |-------------|-----|\n304: | Development | `http://localhost:3000/api` |\n305: | Staging | `https://staging.nestfind.com/api` |\n306: | Production | `https://api.nestfind.com/api` |\n307: \n308: ---\n309: \n310: ## Related Documentation\n311: \n312: - [API Documentation](PROJECT_API.md) — Complete API endpoint specifications\n313: - [Database Schema](PROJECT_DATABASE.md) — Entity definitions and relationships\n314: - [API Integration](PROJECT_API_INTEGRATION.md) — Frontend-backend integration mapping\n315: - [Backend API Status](../status/backend/API_IMPLEMENTATION_STATUS.md) — Backend implementation tracking\n316: - [Frontend Screen Status](../status/frontend/SCREEN_IMPLEMENTATION_STATUS.md) — Frontend implementation tracking\n317: - [Architecture Decisions](../memory/DECISIONS.md) — Key technical decisions log\n318: - [Coding Patterns](../memory/LEARNINGS.md) — Patterns and insights\n319: \n320: ---\n321: \n322: *Generated: 2026-05-19 | Source: seed.yaml + architecture guides*\n\n(End of file - total 322 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# PROJECT_KNOWLEDGE\n\n## Overview\n\n### Application Purpose\n\nNestFind is a streamlined rental property listing platform that connects renters with available properties. The platform focuses exclusively on rentals, providing a clean and efficient browsing experience where renters can search, filter, view details, save favorites, and submit inquiries to property managers. An accompanying admin dashboard enables administrators to manage property listings, respond to inquiries, and oversee user accounts.\n\nThe platform targets two primary user groups: Renters who browse and discover rental properties, and Administrators who manage the listings and respond to renter inquiries. NestFind integrates with Google Maps for property location display.\n\n### Technology Stack\n\n| Layer | Technology |\n|-------|------------|\n| Backend | NestJS 11, TypeScript 5.7+ |\n| Frontend | React 19 with React Router 7 (framework mode) |\n| Database | PostgreSQL 16 |\n| ORM | TypeORM 0.3.x |\n| Authentication | JWT via httpOnly cookies (Access: 1h, Refresh: 7d) |\n| API Documentation | Swagger/OpenAPI |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".claude-project/nestfind/docs/PROJECT_KNOWLEDGE.md","time":{"start":1779187299643,"end":1779187299915}},"id":"prt_e3fd3afdd001u4zdzLzR4PUndk","sessionID":"ses_1c02c7df7ffeSj5NTT2zeCGmCe","messageID":"msg_e3fd3868d001ZEdV2P42jpJWVb"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779187301510,"sessionID":"ses_1c02c7df7ffeSj5NTT2zeCGmCe","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_02_El56EzpPhrIgDJ607Ygr2486","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude-project/nestfind/docs/PROJECT_DATABASE.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude-project/nestfind/docs/PROJECT_DATABASE.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # PROJECT_DATABASE\n2: \n3: ## Schema Overview\n4: \n5: All entities extend `BaseEntity` which provides:\n6: - `id` — UUID primary key\n7: - `createdAt` — `timestamp` (auto-managed)\n8: - `updatedAt` — `timestamp` (auto-managed)\n9: - `deletedAt` — `timestamp | null` (soft delete support)\n10: \n11: Column naming convention: `snake_case` in the database (`@CreateDateColumn({ name: 'created_at' })`).\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Entities\n16: \n17: ### User\n18: \n19: Represents all registered users (Renters and Admins). Extends `BaseEntity` with soft delete.\n20: \n21: **Table:** `users`\n22: \n23: | Field | Type | Constraints | Description |\n24: |-------|------|-------------|-------------|\n25: | `id` | `uuid` | PK, default: `uuid_generate_v4()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n26: | `name` | `varchar(100)` | NOT NULL | User's full name |\n27: | `email` | `varchar(255)` | UNIQUE, NOT NULL | Login email address |\n28: | `password` | `varchar(255)` | NOT NULL | bcrypt-hashed password |\n29: | `phone` | `varchar(20)` | NULLABLE | Optional phone number |\n30: | `role` | `enum` (`RoleEnum`) | NOT NULL, default: `'renter'` | `renter` \\| `admin` |\n31: | `status` | `enum` (`UserStatusEnum`) | NOT NULL, default: `'active'` | `active` \\| `suspended` |\n32: | `email_verified_at` | `timestamp` | NULLABLE | Null until email verification completes |\n33: | `created_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL, default: `now()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n34: | `updated_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL, default: `now()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n35: | `deleted_at` | `timestamp` | NULLABLE | Soft delete timestamp |\n36: \n37: **Indexes:**\n38: - `UNIQUE` on `email`\n39: - `INDEX` on `role`\n40: - `INDEX` on `status`\n41: - `INDEX` on `(role, status)` composite\n42: \n43: **Relationships:**\n44: - `hasMany` → `RefreshToken` (one user has many refresh tokens)\n45: - `hasMany` → `PasswordResetToken` (one user has many reset tokens)\n46: - `hasMany` → `Favorite` (one user has many favorites)\n47: - `hasMany` → `Inquiry` (one user submits many inquiries)\n48: \n49: ---\n50: \n51: ### RefreshToken\n52: \n53: Stores JWT refresh tokens for rotation and invalidation. Each refresh creates a new row; the old row is marked deleted when rotated. Not extending `BaseEntity` (no need for update timestamps or soft delete — expiries handle lifecycle).\n54: \n55: **Table:** `refresh_tokens`\n56: \n57: | Field | Type | Constraints | Description |\n58: |-------|------|-------------|-------------|\n59: | `id` | `uuid` | PK, default: `uuid_generate_v4()` | Primary key |\n60: | `user_id` | `uuid` | FK → `users.id`, NOT NULL, ON DELETE CASCADE | Owning user |\n61: | `token` | `varchar(500)` | NOT NULL, UNIQUE | Encoded JWT refresh token string |\n62: | `expires_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL | Token expiration time (7 days from issue) |\n63: | `revoked_at` | `timestamp` | NULLABLE | Set when token is rotated or user logs out |\n64: | `created_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL, default: `now()` | Token creation time |\n65: \n66: **Indexes:**\n67: - `UNIQUE` on `token`\n68: - `INDEX` on `user_id`\n69: - `INDEX` on `expires_at`\n70: \n71: **Relationships:**\n72: - `belongsTo` → `User` via `user_id`\n73: \n74: ---\n75: \n76: ### PasswordResetToken\n77: \n78: Stores tokens for the forgot-password / reset-password flow. Tokens expire after a configurable window (e.g., 1 hour).\n79: \n80: **Table:** `password_reset_tokens`\n81: \n82: | Field | Type | Constraints | Description |\n83: |-------|------|-------------|-------------|\n84: | `id` | `uuid` | PK, default: `uuid_generate_v4()` | Primary key |\n85: | `user_id` | `uuid` | FK → `users.id`, NOT NULL, ON DELETE CASCADE | Owning user |\n86: | `token` | `varchar(500)` | NOT NULL, UNIQUE | Secure random reset token |\n87: | `expires_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL | Token expiry (e.g., 1 hour from creation) |\n88: | `used_at` | `timestamp` | NULLABLE | Set when password is successfully reset |\n89: | `created_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL, default: `now()` | Token creation time |\n90: \n91: **Indexes:**\n92: - `UNIQUE` on `token`\n93: - `INDEX` on `user_id`\n94: \n95: **Relationships:**\n96: - `belongsTo` → `User` via `user_id`\n97: \n98: ---\n99: \n100: ### Property\n101: \n102: Represents a rental property listing. Supports soft delete (archiving). Address fields are stored as individual columns for search/indexing; API layer nests them into an `address` object.\n103: \n104: **Table:** `properties`\n105: \n106: | Field | Type | Constraints | Description |\n107: |-------|------|-------------|-------------|\n108: | `id` | `uuid` | PK, default: `uuid_generate_v4()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n109: | `title` | `varchar(200)` | NOT NULL | Listing title (5–200 chars) |\n110: | `description` | `text` | NOT NULL | Full description (20–5000 chars) |\n111: | `price` | `decimal(10,2)` | NOT NULL | Monthly rent (> 0) |\n112: | `bedrooms` | `integer` | NOT NULL, CHECK (≥ 0) | Number of bedrooms |\n113: | `bathrooms` | `integer` | NOT NULL, CHECK (≥ 0) | Number of bathrooms |\n114: | `square_feet` | `integer` | NULLABLE, CHECK (> 0) | Living area in square feet |\n115: | `property_type` | `enum` (`PropertyTypeEnum`) | NOT NULL | `apartment` \\| `house` \\| `condo` \\| `townhouse` \\| `studio` |\n116: | `address_street` | `varchar(200)` | NOT NULL | Street address |\n117: | `address_city` | `varchar(100)` | NOT NULL | City |\n118: | `address_state` | `varchar(100)` | NOT NULL | State / province |\n119: | `address_zip_code` | `varchar(10)` | NOT NULL | ZIP / postal code |\n120: | `address_latitude` | `decimal(10,7)` | NULLABLE | Geocoordinate latitude (-90 to 90) |\n121: | `address_longitude` | `decimal(10,7)` | NULLABLE | Geocoordinate longitude (-180 to 180) |\n122: | `available_from` | `date` | NULLABLE | Date property becomes available |\n123: | `created_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL, default: `now()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n124: | `updated_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL, default: `now()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n125: | `deleted_at` | `timestamp` | NULLABLE | Soft delete / archive timestamp |\n126: \n127: **Indexes:**\n128: - `INDEX` on `property_type`\n129: - `INDEX` on `price`\n130: - `INDEX` on `bedrooms`\n131: - `INDEX` on `bathrooms`\n132: - `INDEX` on `address_city`\n133: - `INDEX` on `address_state`\n134: - `INDEX` on `(address_latitude, address_longitude)` — geospatial queries\n135: - `GIN INDEX` or `tsvector` on `title || ' ' || description || ' ' || address_city || ' ' || address_state` for full-text search (optional, for performance at scale)\n136: \n137: **Relationships:**\n138: - `hasMany` → `PropertyPhoto` (one property has many photos)\n139: - `belongsToMany` → `Amenity` via `property_amenities` junction\n140: - `hasMany` → `Favorite` (one property is favorited by many users)\n141: - `hasMany` → `Inquiry` (one property receives many inquiries)\n142: \n143: ---\n144: \n145: ### PropertyPhoto\n146: \n147: Stores uploaded photos for a property. Multiple photos per property with ordering and a primary photo designation.\n148: \n149: **Table:** `property_photos`\n150: \n151: | Field | Type | Constraints | Description |\n152: |-------|------|-------------|-------------|\n153: | `id` | `uuid` | PK, default: `uuid_generate_v4()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n154: | `property_id` | `uuid` | FK → `properties.id`, NOT NULL, ON DELETE CASCADE | Owning property |\n155: | `url` | `varchar(500)` | NOT NULL | Photo URL (S3 / CDN path) |\n156: | `is_primary` | `boolean` | NOT NULL, default: `false` | Whether this is the main/thumbnail photo |\n157: | `sort_order` | `integer` | NOT NULL, default: `0` | Display order in gallery |\n158: | `created_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL, default: `now()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n159: | `updated_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL, default: `now()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n160: \n161: **Indexes:**\n162: - `INDEX` on `property_id`\n163: - `INDEX` on `(property_id, sort_order)`\n164: \n165: **Business Rule:** Only one photo per property may have `is_primary = true`. Enforced at the application layer.\n166: \n167: **Relationships:**\n168: - `belongsTo` → `Property` via `property_id`\n169: \n170: ---\n171: \n172: ### Amenity\n173: \n174: Predefined list of amenities that can be associated with properties. Managed by admins.\n175: \n176: **Table:** `amenities`\n177: \n178: | Field | Type | Constraints | Description |\n179: |-------|------|-------------|-------------|\n180: | `id` | `uuid` | PK, default: `uuid_generate_v4()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n181: | `name` | `varchar(50)` | UNIQUE, NOT NULL | Amenity name (e.g., \"parking\", \"gym\") |\n182: | `icon` | `varchar(50)` | NOT NULL | Icon identifier for frontend rendering |\n183: | `created_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL, default: `now()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n184: | `updated_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL, default: `now()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n185: | `deleted_at` | `timestamp` | NULLABLE | Soft delete |\n186: \n187: **Indexes:**\n188: - `UNIQUE` on `name`\n189: \n190: **Relationships:**\n191: - `belongsToMany` → `Property` via `property_amenities` junction\n192: \n193: ---\n194: \n195: ### PropertyAmenity\n196: \n197: Junction table for the many-to-many relationship between `Property` and `Amenity`. Each row links one property to one amenity.\n198: \n199: **Table:** `property_amenities`\n200: \n201: | Field | Type | Constraints | Description |\n202: |-------|------|-------------|-------------|\n203: | `property_id` | `uuid` | PK (composite), FK → `properties.id`, NOT NULL, ON DELETE CASCADE | Property reference |\n204: | `amenity_id` | `uuid` | PK (composite), FK → `amenities.id`, NOT NULL, ON DELETE CASCADE | Amenity reference |\n205: \n206: **Primary Key:** Composite `(property_id, amenity_id)`\n207: \n208: **Indexes:**\n209: - `INDEX` on `amenity_id`\n210: \n211: **Relationships:**\n212: - `belongsTo` → `Property` via `property_id`\n213: - `belongsTo` → `Amenity` via `amenity_id`\n214: \n215: ---\n216: \n217: ### Favorite\n218: \n219: Represents a renter saving a property to their favorites. Idempotent — adding a duplicate returns the existing record (API handles this). Composite unique constraint prevents duplicates.\n220: \n221: **Table:** `favorites`\n222: \n223: | Field | Type | Constraints | Description |\n224: |-------|------|-------------|-------------|\n225: | `id` | `uuid` | PK, default: `uuid_generate_v4()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n226: | `user_id` | `uuid` | FK → `users.id`, NOT NULL, ON DELETE CASCADE | The renter who favorited |\n227: | `property_id` | `uuid` | FK → `properties.id`, NOT NULL, ON DELETE CASCADE | The favorited property |\n228: | `created_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL, default: `now()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n229: \n230: **Indexes:**\n231: - `UNIQUE` on `(user_id, property_id)` — prevents duplicate favorites\n232: - `INDEX` on `user_id`\n233: - `INDEX` on `property_id`\n234: \n235: **Relationships:**\n236: - `belongsTo` → `User` via `user_id`\n237: - `belongsTo` → `Property` via `property_id`\n238: \n239: ---\n240: \n241: ### Inquiry\n242: \n243: Represents a contact/inquiry submission from a renter about a specific property. Admins manage inquiry status and responses.\n244: \n245: **Table:** `inquiries`\n246: \n247: | Field | Type | Constraints | Description |\n248: |-------|------|-------------|-------------|\n249: | `id` | `uuid` | PK, default: `uuid_generate_v4()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n250: | `property_id` | `uuid` | FK → `properties.id`, NOT NULL, ON DELETE SET NULL | Subject property |\n251: | `user_id` | `uuid` | FK → `users.id`, NOT NULL, ON DELETE SET NULL | Submitting renter |\n252: | `name` | `varchar(100)` | NOT NULL | Submitter's name (denormalized for display) |\n253: | `email` | `varchar(255)` | NOT NULL | Submitter's email (denormalized) |\n254: | `phone` | `varchar(20)` | NULLABLE | Submitter's phone (denormalized) |\n255: | `message` | `text` | NOT NULL | Inquiry message body (10–2000 chars) |\n256: | `status` | `enum` (`InquiryStatusEnum`) | NOT NULL, default: `'new'` | `new` \\| `read` \\| `responded` |\n257: | `response` | `text` | NULLABLE | Admin's response text |\n258: | `responded_at` | `timestamp` | NULLABLE | Set when admin responds |\n259: | `created_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL, default: `now()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n260: | `updated_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL, default: `now()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n261: \n262: **Note:** `name`, `email`, `phone` are denormalized from the `User` record at submission time. This preserves the inquiry even if the user account is later deleted (hence `ON DELETE SET NULL` on `user_id`).\n263: \n264: **Indexes:**\n265: - `INDEX` on `property_id`\n266: - `INDEX` on `user_id`\n267: - `INDEX` on `status`\n268: - `INDEX` on `(status, created_at)` — for admin dashboard filtering\n269: \n270: **Relationships:**\n271: - `belongsTo` → `Property` via `property_id`\n272: - `belongsTo` → `User` via `user_id`\n273: \n274: ---\n275: \n276: ## Enums\n277: \n278: ### RoleEnum\n279: \n280: Used in `users.role`.\n281: \n282: | Value | Description |\n283: |-------|-------------|\n284: | `renter` | Standard user who browses and saves properties, submits inquiries |\n285: | `admin` | Administrator with full system access |\n286: \n287: ---\n288: \n289: ### UserStatusEnum\n290: \n291: Used in `users.status`.\n292: \n293: | Value | Description |\n294: |-------|-------------|\n295: | `active` | Account in good standing |\n296: | `suspended` | Account suspended by admin; cannot log in |\n297: \n298: ---\n299: \n300: ### PropertyTypeEnum\n301: \n302: Used in `properties.property_type`.\n303: \n304: | Value | Description |\n305: |-------|-------------|\n306: | `apartment` | Apartment unit |\n307: | `house` | Single-family house |\n308: | `condo` | Condominium |\n309: | `townhouse` | Townhouse |\n310: | `studio` | Studio apartment |\n311: \n312: ---\n313: \n314: ### InquiryStatusEnum\n315: \n316: Used in `inquiries.status`.\n317: \n318: | Value | Description |\n319: |-------|-------------|\n320: | `new` | Unread inquiry (default on submission) |\n321: | `read` | Viewed by admin |\n322: | `responded` | Admin has sent a response |\n323: \n324: ---\n325: \n326: ## Relationships\n327: \n328: ### Entity Relationship Diagram\n329: \n330: ```\n331: users (1) ────────< (many) refresh_tokens\n332: users (1) ────────< (many) password_reset_tokens\n333: users (1) ────────< (many) favorites\n334: users (1) ────────< (many) inquiries\n335: \n336: properties (1) ───< (many) property_photos\n337: properties (1) ───< (many) favorites\n338: properties (1) ───< (many) inquiries\n339: properties (many) >────< (many) amenities  [via property_amenities]\n340: ```\n341: \n342: ### Foreign Key Summary\n343: \n344: | Child Table | FK Column | Parent Table | On Delete |\n345: |-------------|----------|--------------|-----------|\n346: | `refresh_tokens` | `user_id` | `users.id` | CASCADE |\n347: | `password_reset_tokens` | `user_id` | `users.id` | CASCADE |\n348: | `property_photos` | `property_id` | `properties.id` | CASCADE |\n349: | `property_amenities` | `property_id` | `properties.id` | CASCADE |\n350: | `property_amenities` | `amenity_id` | `amenities.id` | CASCADE |\n351: | `favorites` | `user_id` | `users.id` | CASCADE |\n352: | `favorites` | `property_id` | `properties.id` | CASCADE |\n353: | `inquiries` | `property_id` | `properties.id` | SET NULL |\n354: | `inquiries` | `user_id` | `users.id` | SET NULL |\n355: \n356: ### Relationship Details\n357: \n358: | Relationship | Type | Owner | Inverse | Junction |\n359: |-------------|------|-------|---------|----------|\n360: | User → RefreshToken | One-to-Many | — | RefreshToken.user ↔ User.refreshTokens | — |\n361: | User → PasswordResetToken | One-to-Many | — | PasswordResetToken.user ↔ User.resetTokens | — |\n362: | User → Favorite | One-to-Many | — | Favorite.user ↔ User.favorites | — |\n363: | User → Inquiry | One-to-Many | — | Inquiry.user ↔ User.inquiries | — |\n364: | Property → PropertyPhoto | One-to-Many | — | PropertyPhoto.property ↔ Property.photos | — |\n365: | Property → Favorite | One-to-Many | — | Favorite.property ↔ Property.favorites | — |\n366: | Property → Inquiry | One-to-Many | — | Inquiry.property ↔ Property.inquiries | — |\n367: | Property ↔ Amenity | Many-to-Many | Property (JoinTable) | Property.amenities ↔ Amenity.properties | `property_amenities` |\n368: \n369: ---\n370: \n371: ## Conventions\n372: \n373: ### Timestamps\n374: - All `timestamp` columns use `default: now()` for `created_at`.\n375: - `updated_at` is auto-managed by TypeORM (`@UpdateDateColumn`).\n376: - `deleted_at` is managed by TypeORM soft-delete (`@DeleteDateColumn`).\n377: \n378: ### Soft Delete\n379: - Enabled on: `users`, `properties`, `amenities`.\n380: - NOT enabled on: `refresh_tokens` (managed via `revoked_at` + `expires_at`), `password_reset_tokens` (managed via `expires_at` + `used_at`), `favorites` (hard delete on unfavorite), `inquiries` (retained indefinitely for audit), `property_photos` (hard delete on removal), `property_amenities` (junction – hard delete on unlink).\n381: \n382: ### Naming\n383: - **Tables**: `snake_case` plural (e.g., `property_photos`, `password_reset_tokens`)\n384: - **Columns**: `snake_case` (e.g., `user_id`, `property_type`, `address_city`)\n385: - **Enums**: PascalCase suffix `Enum` in TypeScript (e.g., `RoleEnum`, `PropertyTypeEnum`)\n386: \n387: ### Data Types\n388: - Monetary values: `decimal(10,2)` (supports prices up to $99,999,999.99)\n389: - Geo-coordinates: `decimal(10,7)` (sub-meter precision)\n390: - Percentages/ratios: `decimal(5,2)` if needed in future\n391: \n392: ---\n393: \n394: *Generated: 2026-05-19 | Source: PROJECT_KNOWLEDGE.md + PROJECT_API.md + database-patterns.md*\n\n(End of file - total 394 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# PROJECT_DATABASE\n\n## Schema Overview\n\nAll entities extend `BaseEntity` which provides:\n- `id` — UUID primary key\n- `createdAt` — `timestamp` (auto-managed)\n- `updatedAt` — `timestamp` (auto-managed)\n- `deletedAt` — `timestamp | null` (soft delete support)\n\nColumn naming convention: `snake_case` in the database (`@CreateDateColumn({ name: 'created_at' })`).\n\n---\n\n## Entities\n\n### User\n\nRepresents all registered users (Renters and Admins). Extends `BaseEntity` with soft delete.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".claude-project/nestfind/docs/PROJECT_DATABASE.md","time":{"start":1779187301239,"end":1779187301508}},"id":"prt_e3fd3b657001Lr1CsNszNtwG0z","sessionID":"ses_1c02c7df7ffeSj5NTT2zeCGmCe","messageID":"msg_e3fd3868d001ZEdV2P42jpJWVb"}}
