{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779187677665,"sessionID":"ses_1c02c7df7ffeSj5NTT2zeCGmCe","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_00_ef5KivzbcJ1z0QqMlMBt9038","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore backend codebase structure","subagent_type":"explore","prompt":"Very thoroughly explore the NestJS backend codebase at /Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/. I need to understand:\n\n1. What modules already exist under backend/src/modules/ (list all)\n2. What base classes exist (backend/src/core/base/) - read each file\n3. What decorators exist (backend/src/core/decorators/) - read each file and their index.ts\n4. What guards exist (backend/src/core/guards/) - read each file\n5. What shared DTOs exist (backend/src/shared/dtos/)\n6. What enums exist (search for *.enum.ts files)\n7. What entities exist under all modules (search for *.entity.ts files)\n8. Read the app.module.ts to see what's already registered\n9. Read the main.ts file\n10. Read the backend/src/core/base/index.ts to see exports\n\nReturn ALL file contents for items 2-5 and 7, and the full directory listing for item 1. Also return any test files related to admin (search backend/test/ for admin-related files)."},"output":"task_id: ses_1c02be329ffejO4rz0bn5aOQAl (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nHere is the complete exploration of the NestJS backend codebase.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Modules under `backend/src/modules/` (5 modules)\n\n```\nmodules/\n├── auth/\n│   └── entities/          (only entities exist; no controllers/services/repos/DTOs yet)\n├── users/\n│   └── entities/          (only entities exist)\n├── properties/\n│   └── entities/          (only entities exist)\n├── favorites/\n│   └── entities/          (only entities exist)\n└── inquiries/\n    └── entities/          (only entities exist)\n```\n\n**Key observation:** Each module only contains an `entities/` subdirectory. No controllers, services, repositories, DTOs, or module files exist yet. The modules are essentially \"entity-only\" at this stage.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Base Classes (`backend/src/core/base/`)\n\n### `base.entity.ts` — `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/core/base/base.entity.ts`\n\n```typescript\nimport {\n    PrimaryGeneratedColumn,\n    CreateDateColumn,\n    UpdateDateColumn,\n    DeleteDateColumn,\n} from 'typeorm';\n\nexport abstract class BaseEntity {\n    @PrimaryGeneratedColumn('uuid')\n    id: string;\n\n    @CreateDateColumn({ name: 'created_at', type: 'timestamp' })\n    createdAt: Date;\n\n    @UpdateDateColumn({ name: 'updated_at', type: 'timestamp' })\n    updatedAt: Date;\n\n    @DeleteDateColumn({ name: 'deleted_at', type: 'timestamp', nullable: true })\n    deletedAt: Date | null;\n}\n```\n\nProvides: `id` (UUID), `createdAt`, `updatedAt`, `deletedAt` (soft-delete support).\n\n---\n\n### `base.repository.ts` — `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/core/base/base.repository.ts`\n\n```typescript\nimport {\n    Repository, FindManyOptions, FindOneOptions, DeepPartial,\n    FindOptionsRelations, QueryDeepPartialEntity,\n} from 'typeorm';\nimport { BaseEntity } from './base.entity';\n\nexport abstract class BaseRepository<T extends BaseEntity> {\n    constructor(protected readonly repository: Repository<T>) {}\n\n    async findAll(options?: FindManyOptions<T>): Promise<T[]> {\n        return this.repository.find(options);\n    }\n    async findById(id: string, relations?: FindOptionsRelations<T>): Promise<T | null> {\n        return this.repository.findOne({\n            where: { id } as unknown as FindOneOptions<T>['where'], relations,\n        });\n    }\n    async findOne(options: FindOneOptions<T>): Promise<T | null> {\n        return this.repository.findOne(options);\n    }\n    async create(data: DeepPartial<T>): Promise<T> {\n        const entity = this.repository.create(data);\n        return this.repository.save(entity);\n    }\n    async update(id: string, data: DeepPartial<T>): Promise<T | null> {\n        await this.repository.update(id, data as QueryDeepPartialEntity<T>);\n        return this.findById(id);\n    }\n    async softDelete(id: string): Promise<void> {\n        await this.repository.softDelete(id);\n    }\n    async delete(id: string): Promise<void> {\n        await this.repository.delete(id);\n    }\n    async count(options?: FindManyOptions<T>): Promise<number> {\n        return this.repository.count(options);\n    }\n}\n```\n\nProvides: Wrapper around TypeORM `Repository` with `findAll`, `findById`, `findOne`, `create`, `update`, `softDelete`, `delete`, `count`.\n\n---\n\n### `base.service.ts` — `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/core/base/base.service.ts`\n\n```typescript\nimport { NotFoundException } from '@nestjs/common';\nimport { FindManyOptions, DeepPartial, FindOptionsRelations } from 'typeorm';\nimport { BaseRepository } from './base.repository';\nimport { BaseEntity } from './base.entity';\n\nexport abstract class BaseService<T extends BaseEntity> {\n    constructor(\n        protected readonly repository: BaseRepository<T>,\n        protected readonly entityName: string,\n    ) {}\n    protected defaultRelations?: FindOptionsRelations<T>;\n\n    async findByIdOrFail(id: string, relations?: FindOptionsRelations<T>): Promise<T> {\n        const entity = await this.repository.findById(id, relations || this.defaultRelations);\n        if (!entity) {\n            throw new NotFoundException(`${this.entityName} with ID ${id} not found`);\n        }\n        return entity;\n    }\n    async findAll(options?: FindManyOptions<T>): Promise<T[]> {\n        return this.repository.findAll({\n            ...options,\n            relations: (options?.relations as FindOptionsRelations<T>) || this.defaultRelations,\n        });\n    }\n    async create(data: DeepPartial<T>): Promise<T> { return this.repository.create(data); }\n    async update(id: string, data: DeepPartial<T>): Promise<T | null> {\n        await this.findByIdOrFail(id);\n        return this.repository.update(id, data);\n    }\n    async remove(id: string): Promise<void> {\n        await this.findByIdOrFail(id);\n        await this.repository.softDelete(id);\n    }\n    async delete(id: string): Promise<void> {\n        await this.findByIdOrFail(id);\n        await this.repository.delete(id);\n    }\n}\n```\n\nProvides: Business logic layer wrapping `BaseRepository` with `findByIdOrFail` (throws NotFoundException), `findAll`, `create`, `update`, `remove` (soft-delete), `delete` (hard-delete). Has a `defaultRelations` property for eager-loading relations.\n\n---\n\n### `base.controller.ts` — `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/core/base/base.controller.ts`\n\n```typescript\nimport { Get, Post, Patch, Delete, Body, Param, Query, HttpCode, HttpStatus, ParseUUIDPipe } from '@nestjs/common';\nimport { ApiOperation, ApiResponse, ApiParam, ApiQuery } from '@nestjs/swagger';\nimport { BaseService } from './base.service';\nimport { BaseEntity } from './base.entity';\nimport { DeepPartial } from 'typeorm';\n\nexport abstract class BaseController<\n    T extends BaseEntity,\n    CreateDto extends DeepPartial<T> = DeepPartial<T>,\n    UpdateDto extends DeepPartial<T> = DeepPartial<T>,\n> {\n    constructor(protected readonly service: BaseService<T>) {}\n\n    @Post()\n    @HttpCode(HttpStatus.CREATED)\n    async create(@Body() createDto: CreateDto): Promise<T> { return this.service.create(createDto); }\n\n    @Get()\n    @HttpCode(HttpStatus.OK)\n    async findAll(@Query('page') page?: number, @Query('limit') limit?: number): Promise<T[]> {\n        const options = page && limit ? { skip: (page - 1) * limit, take: limit } : {};\n        return this.service.findAll(options);\n    }\n\n    @Get(':id')\n    @HttpCode(HttpStatus.OK)\n    async findOne(@Param('id', ParseUUIDPipe) id: string): Promise<T> {\n        return this.service.findByIdOrFail(id);\n    }\n\n    @Patch(':id')\n    @HttpCode(HttpStatus.OK)\n    async update(@Param('id', ParseUUIDPipe) id: string, @Body() updateDto: UpdateDto): Promise<T | null> {\n        return this.service.update(id, updateDto);\n    }\n\n    @Delete(':id')\n    @HttpCode(HttpStatus.OK)\n    async remove(@Param('id', ParseUUIDPipe) id: string): Promise<void> {\n        return this.service.remove(id);\n    }\n}\n```\n\nProvides: Full REST CRUD endpoints (`POST /`, `GET /`, `GET /:id`, `PATCH /:id`, `DELETE /:id`) with UUID validation and Swagger docs. Generic over entity, create-DTO, and update-DTO types.\n\n---\n\n### `index.ts` (base exports) — `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/core/base/index.ts`\n\n```typescript\nexport { BaseEntity } from './base.entity';\nexport { BaseRepository } from './base.repository';\nexport { BaseService } from './base.service';\nexport { BaseController } from './base.controller';\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. Decorators (`backend/src/core/decorators/`)\n\n### `index.ts` — `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/core/decorators/index.ts`\n\n```typescript\nexport { Public, IS_PUBLIC_KEY } from './public.decorator';\nexport { Roles, ROLES_KEY } from './roles.decorator';\nexport { CurrentUser } from './current-user.decorator';\nexport { ApiSwagger } from './api-swagger.decorator';\nexport { ApiResponseData } from './api-response-data.decorator';\n```\n\n---\n\n### `public.decorator.ts` — `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/core/decorators/public.decorator.ts`\n\n```typescript\nimport { SetMetadata } from '@nestjs/common';\nexport const IS_PUBLIC_KEY = 'isPublic';\nexport const Public = () => SetMetadata(IS_PUBLIC_KEY, true);\n```\n\nMarks a route as public (skips JWT authentication via `JwtAuthGuard`).\n\n---\n\n### `roles.decorator.ts` — `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/core/decorators/roles.decorator.ts`\n\n```typescript\nimport { SetMetadata } from '@nestjs/common';\nexport const ROLES_KEY = 'roles';\n\n/**\n * Mark a route with required roles.\n * Uses string[] to stay generic — projects can narrow to their own RoleEnum after copying.\n * Usage: @Roles('admin', 'manager')\n */\nexport const Roles = (...roles: string[]) => SetMetadata(ROLES_KEY, roles);\n```\n\n---\n\n### `current-user.decorator.ts` — `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/core/decorators/current-user.decorator.ts`\n\n```typescript\nimport { createParamDecorator, ExecutionContext } from '@nestjs/common';\n\n/**\n * Extract the current authenticated user from the request.\n * Usage:\n *   @CurrentUser() user: IJwtPayload          — full user object\n *   @CurrentUser('id') userId: string          — specific field\n */\nexport const CurrentUser = createParamDecorator(\n    (data: string | undefined, ctx: ExecutionContext) => {\n        const request = ctx.switchToHttp().getRequest();\n        const user = request.user;\n        return data ? user?.[data] : user;\n    },\n);\n```\n\n---\n\n### `api-swagger.decorator.ts` — `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/core/decorators/api-swagger.decorator.ts`\n\nA comprehensive Swagger decorator builder (231 lines). It:\n- Accepts an `ApiSwaggerOptions` config object with: `resourceName`, `requestDto`, `responseDto`, `successStatus`, `isArray`, `requiresAuth`, `errors`, `operation` (create/getAll/getOne/update/delete/search/count/custom), `summary`, `paramName`, `withPagination`\n- Auto-generates summaries based on operation type\n- Adds pagination query params (`page`, `limit`, `search`, `sortBy`, `sortOrder`) when `withPagination: true`\n- Adds `@ApiBearerAuth()` + `@ApiCookieAuth(\"access_token\")` when `requiresAuth: true`\n- Auto-generates error responses (400, 401, 404, 409) based on operation type\n- Uses `applyDecorators` to compose all decorators\n\n---\n\n### `api-response-data.decorator.ts` — `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/core/decorators/api-response-data.decorator.ts`\n\n```typescript\nimport { applyDecorators, Type } from '@nestjs/common';\nimport { ApiExtraModels, ApiResponse, getSchemaPath } from '@nestjs/swagger';\nimport { ResponsePayloadDto } from '../../shared/dtos';\n\nexport function ApiResponseData<T extends Type<any>>(dto: T, status = 200, isArray = false) {\n    return applyDecorators(\n        ApiExtraModels(ResponsePayloadDto, dto),\n        ApiResponse({\n            status,\n            description: 'Successful response',\n            schema: {\n                allOf: [\n                    { $ref: getSchemaPath(ResponsePayloadDto) },\n                    {\n                        properties: {\n                            data: isArray\n                                ? { type: 'array', items: { $ref: getSchemaPath(dto) } }\n                                : { $ref: getSchemaPath(dto) },\n                        },\n                    },\n                ],\n            },\n        }),\n    );\n}\n```\n\nWraps a DTO inside the `ResponsePayloadDto.data` schema for consistent Swagger documentation.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Guards (`backend/src/core/guards/`)\n\n### `index.ts` — `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/core/guards/index.ts`\n\n```typescript\nexport { JwtAuthGuard } from './jwt-auth.guard';\nexport { RolesGuard } from './roles.guard';\nexport { JwtStrategy } from './jwt.strategy';\n```\n\n---\n\n### `jwt-auth.guard.ts` — `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/core/guards/jwt-auth.guard.ts`\n\n```typescript\nimport { Injectable, ExecutionContext, UnauthorizedException } from '@nestjs/common';\nimport { AuthGuard } from '@nestjs/passport';\nimport { Reflector } from '@nestjs/core';\nimport { IS_PUBLIC_KEY } from '../decorators/public.decorator';\n\n@Injectable()\nexport class JwtAuthGuard extends AuthGuard('jwt') {\n    constructor(private reflector: Reflector) { super(); }\n\n    canActivate(context: ExecutionContext) {\n        const isPublic = this.reflector.getAllAndOverride<boolean>(IS_PUBLIC_KEY,\n            [context.getHandler(), context.getClass()]);\n        if (isPublic) return true;             // Skip auth for @Public() routes\n        return super.canActivate(context);      // Execute Passport JWT strategy\n    }\n\n    handleRequest(err: any, user: any, info: any) {\n        if (err || !user) throw err || new UnauthorizedException('Invalid or expired token');\n        return user;\n    }\n}\n```\n\nSkips authentication for `@Public()` routes, runs JWT validation via Passport for all others.\n\n---\n\n### `roles.guard.ts` — `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/core/guards/roles.guard.ts`\n\n```typescript\nimport { Injectable, CanActivate, ExecutionContext } from '@nestjs/common';\nimport { Reflector } from '@nestjs/core';\nimport { ROLES_KEY } from '../decorators/roles.decorator';\n\n@Injectable()\nexport class RolesGuard implements CanActivate {\n    constructor(private reflector: Reflector) {}\n\n    canActivate(context: ExecutionContext): boolean {\n        const requiredRoles = this.reflector.getAllAndOverride<string[]>(ROLES_KEY,\n            [context.getHandler(), context.getClass()]);\n        if (!requiredRoles) return true; // No roles required\n\n        const { user } = context.switchToHttp().getRequest();\n        // Supports user.role (single) or user.roles (array)\n        if (Array.isArray(user?.roles)) {\n            return requiredRoles.some((role) => user.roles.includes(role));\n        }\n        return requiredRoles.some((role) => user?.role === role);\n    }\n}\n```\n\nChecks `@Roles()` metadata against `user.role` or `user.roles` from the JWT payload.\n\n---\n\n### `jwt.strategy.ts` — `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/core/guards/jwt.strategy.ts`\n\n```typescript\nimport { Injectable, UnauthorizedException } from \"@nestjs/common\";\nimport { PassportStrategy } from \"@nestjs/passport\";\nimport { ExtractJwt, Strategy } from \"passport-jwt\";\nimport { Request } from \"express\";\nimport { envConfigService } from \"../../config/env-config.service\";\n\n@Injectable()\nexport class JwtStrategy extends PassportStrategy(Strategy) {\n  constructor() {\n    super({\n      jwtFromRequest: ExtractJwt.fromExtractors([\n        JwtStrategy.extractJWTFromCookie,          // Cookie first (httpOnly)\n        ExtractJwt.fromAuthHeaderAsBearerToken(),   // Fallback to Bearer header\n      ]),\n      ignoreExpiration: false,\n      secretOrKey: envConfigService.getAuthJWTConfig().AUTH_JWT_SECRET,\n    });\n  }\n\n  private static extractJWTFromCookie(this: void, req: Request): string | null {\n    const cookieName = envConfigService.getAuthJWTConfig().AUTH_TOKEN_COOKIE_NAME;\n    if (req.cookies && req.cookies[cookieName]) return req.cookies[cookieName];\n    return null;\n  }\n\n  validate(payload: any) {\n    if (!payload.id && !payload.sub) throw new UnauthorizedException(\"Invalid token payload\");\n    return { id: payload.sub || payload.id, email: payload.email, role: payload.role };\n  }\n}\n```\n\nExtracts JWT from httpOnly cookie first, falls back to Bearer header. Returns `{ id, email, role }` to `request.user`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Shared DTOs (`backend/src/shared/dtos/`)\n\n### `index.ts` — `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/shared/dtos/index.ts`\n\n```typescript\nexport { ResponsePayloadDto, ErrorDetailDto, SuccessResponseDto, ErrorResponseDto,\n         PaginationMetaDto, PaginatedResponseDto } from './response-payload.dto';\nexport { PaginationDto } from './pagination.dto';\n```\n\n---\n\n### `response-payload.dto.ts` — `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/shared/dtos/response-payload.dto.ts`\n\nContains 6 classes:\n- **`ErrorDetailDto`** — `field?`, `reason?`, `constraints?` (Record<string,string>), `code?`\n- **`ResponsePayloadDto<T>`** — `success: boolean`, `statusCode: number`, `message: string`, `data?: T`, `error?: ErrorDetailDto[]`, `timestamp?: string`, `path?: string` (with constructor that sets timestamp)\n- **`SuccessResponseDto<T>`** — extends `ResponsePayloadDto<T>`, constructor sets `success: true`\n- **`ErrorResponseDto`** — extends `ResponsePayloadDto`, constructor sets `success: false`\n- **`PaginationMetaDto`** — `page`, `limit`, `total`, `totalPages`, `hasNextPage`, `hasPreviousPage` (constructor computes `totalPages`, `hasNextPage`, `hasPreviousPage`)\n- **`PaginatedResponseDto<T>`** — extends `ResponsePayloadDto<T[]>` with `meta: PaginationMetaDto`\n\n---\n\n### `pagination.dto.ts` — `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/shared/dtos/pagination.dto.ts`\n\n```typescript\nimport { IsOptional, IsInt, Min, Max, IsIn, IsString } from 'class-validator';\nimport { Type } from 'class-transformer';\n\nexport class PaginationDto {\n    @IsOptional() @Type(() => Number) @IsInt() @Min(1)\n    page?: number = 1;\n\n    @IsOptional() @Type(() => Number) @IsInt() @Min(1) @Max(100)\n    limit?: number = 10;\n\n    @IsOptional() @IsString()\n    sortBy?: string;\n\n    @IsOptional() @IsIn(['ASC', 'DESC'])\n    sortOrder?: 'ASC' | 'DESC' = 'DESC';\n\n    @IsOptional() @IsString()\n    search?: string;\n}\n```\n\nA reusable pagination/query DTO for `GET` list endpoints.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Enums (`backend/src/common/enums/`)\n\n| File | Absolute Path | Contents |\n|------|--------------|----------|\n| `role.enum.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/common/enums/role.enum.ts` | `RENTER = 'renter'`, `ADMIN = 'admin'` |\n| `user-status.enum.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/common/enums/user-status.enum.ts` | `ACTIVE = 'active'`, `SUSPENDED = 'suspended'` |\n| `property-type.enum.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/common/enums/property-type.enum.ts` | `APARTMENT`, `HOUSE`, `CONDO`, `TOWNHOUSE`, `STUDIO` |\n| `inquiry-status.enum.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/common/enums/inquiry-status.enum.ts` | `NEW`, `READ`, `RESPONDED` |\n\n---\n\n## 7. Entities (all `*.entity.ts` files, 9 total)\n\n### Module: `users`\n**`user.entity.ts`** — `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/modules/users/entities/user.entity.ts`\n- Table: `users`\n- Extends `BaseEntity`\n- Columns: `name` (varchar 100), `email` (varchar 255, unique), `password` (varchar 255), `phone` (varchar 20, nullable), `role` (enum `RoleEnum`, default RENTER, indexed), `status` (enum `UserStatusEnum`, default ACTIVE, indexed), `emailVerifiedAt` (timestamp, nullable)\n- Relations: `OneToMany` → `RefreshToken[]`, `PasswordResetToken[]`, `Favorite[]`, `Inquiry[]`\n- Indexes: composite `[role, status]`\n\n### Module: `auth`\n**`refresh-token.entity.ts`** — `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/modules/auth/entities/refresh-token.entity.ts`\n- Table: `refresh_tokens`\n- Does NOT extend `BaseEntity` (has its own `id`, `createdAt`)\n- Columns: `userId` (uuid), `token` (varchar 500, unique), `expiresAt` (timestamp), `revokedAt` (timestamp, nullable)\n- Relation: `ManyToOne → User` (CASCADE delete)\n- Indexes: `[userId]`, `[expiresAt]`\n\n**`password-reset-token.entity.ts`** — `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/modules/auth/entities/password-reset-token.entity.ts`\n- Table: `password_reset_tokens`\n- Does NOT extend `BaseEntity`\n- Columns: `userId` (uuid), `token` (varchar 500, unique), `expiresAt` (timestamp), `usedAt` (timestamp, nullable)\n- Relation: `ManyToOne → User` (CASCADE delete)\n- Indexes: `[userId]`\n\n### Module: `properties`\n**`property.entity.ts`** — `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/modules/properties/entities/property.entity.ts`\n- Table: `properties`\n- Extends `BaseEntity`\n- Columns: `title` (varchar 200), `description` (text), `price` (decimal 10,2), `bedrooms` (int), `bathrooms` (int), `squareFeet` (int, nullable)